title: twice-cooked divinity
directions: Stir sugar into corn syrup, water and dash of salt until dissolved.
Boil to medium ball stage (240°).
Slowly pour 1/3 over beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remaining syrup to very hard ball stage (265°).
Test.
Add several drops to water.
Beat syrup in candy mixture.
Continue beating.
When mixture holds its shape from a spoon, add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.

title: stromboli sandwiches
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until thoroughly hot.
Spread on bottom half of bun, sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of mixture and place other half of bun on top.
Wrap in foil; bake 10 minutes at 400°.
(Can be done in microwave.)

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in small saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly. Set aside to cool. Beat eggs until thick and light in color. Gradually add sugar, beating until thickened. Add baking powder, salt and flour. Blend in cooled chocolate mixture, nuts, vanilla and almond extract. Spread half of chocolate batter in greased 8 or 9-inch square pan. Cover with Cream Cheese Batter.

title: berry-yum bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, brown sugar, oat and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until it resembles coarse crumbs. Toss mixture with yams and cranberries, place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and broil until light brown.

title: red satin punch
directions: Fill ice cube trays with lemon-lime beverage, reserving remainder
for
punch; freeze.
At serving time, combine cranberry juice
and
apple	juice
in
punch
bowl.
Slowly pour remaining lemon-lime beverage and prepared ice cubes.
Yield: 35 servings.

title: homemade pancakes(pancakes are perfect for brunch)
directions: Dump everything into a bowl (egg and shortening last) and beat a bit, but not too much.
Batter should be a little lumpy.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Cream together sugar and butter, then add milk, flour and baking powder.
Mix well and put in a 2-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: golden ham casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in a small amount of boiling unsalted water until crisp-tender. Drain and set aside.

title: gazpacho
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop.
Mix tomatoes, cucumber, green pepper and onions.
Stir vegetable juice cocktail, vinegar, olive oil, garlic salt, basil and hot pepper sauce into tomato mixture. Cover and chill for several hours before serving.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cut tortillas into strips and fry in oil until crispy.
Set aside.
Blend tomatoes, garlic and onion in blender until smooth puree.
Saute puree in 2 tablespoons oil, then add bouillon cubes and let boil 1 minute.
Add broth.
Cover and simmer.
Add pepper to taste after 20 minutes.
Add cilantro and turn off heat.

title: korean marinade
directions: This marinade is enough for about 5 pounds short ribs or 6 pounds sliced rib eye steak.
Marinate at least 8 hours or overnight, turning meat occasionally.

title: raw apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 cup Bundt pan at 350° for one hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl except nuts.
Microwave until chips are melted, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring once or twice. During cooling, stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased square pan. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: avocado and tomato salad
directions: In a large serving bowl, toss together the tomatoes, avocados and red onion.
Dust lightly with black pepper and pour salad dressing over.
Cover and chill for at least one hour before serving to blend flavors.

title: cheese ball
directions: You can use fat-free ingredients.

title: marinade
directions: Mix together.
Great on steak, shrimp or chicken.

title: irresistable brownies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients until smooth and well blended.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup more chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: sweet tortillas
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a big bowl.

title: baked beans
directions: Add last.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Separate cauliflower into bite-size flowerets.
Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Add mayo or salad dressing, tossing to coat vegetables.
Chill several hours before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix together wafers and 1 stick margarine and spread in bottom of Pyrex dish to form crust.
Mix together egg whites, 1 stick margarine and powdered sugar.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas longways and lay over filling.
Spread pineapple over bananas. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle pecan chips and cherries over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut fruit in bite-size pieces.
Sprinkle with sugar to taste. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Can be made ahead, but add bananas just before serving.
Easy and delicious.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together oil, vinegar, wine, onion powder, salt and pepper to make dressing.
Pour over spinach, bacon and sliced eggs.

title: apple brown betty
directions: With a fork, lightly toss bread crumbs with melted butter. Combine sugar, cinnamon, lemon juice and rind to form a paste. Line the bottom of a buttered casserole dish with approximately 1/3 of the bread crumb mixture.
Spread half of the apples over the crumbs, then half the paste over the apples.
Repeat this process with crumbs as final layer.
Pour orange juice evenly over apple mixture.

title: elegant seafood quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll pastry to 13-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Place in 10-inch pie plate or casserole dish.
Turn under edge; flute.
Sprinkle cheese, crab or Sea Legs, onion, flour and seasonings in pie plate or dish.
Beat together eggs and half and half.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake 55 or 60 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cranberry-apple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (moderate).
Grease 7 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine cranberry sauce and apples.
Spread in baking pan. Combine rolled oats, brown sugar, salt and flour.
Add melted fat and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook chicken in small amount of oil in wok or skillet on medium high heat.
Heat for 4 to 6 minutes until done.
Add stir- fry mix and vegetables.
Cook for additional 5 to 7 minutes, stirring very often.
Add water and/or soy sauce as needed.
Serve over white or brown rice.
(Vegetables may be substituted to taste.)

title: refrigerator coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut together and put in refrigerator to soak for 4 hours.
Mix and bake cake mix according to directions on box.
Split 2 layers to make 4 layers.
Spread sour cream mixture between layers.
Ice entire cake with Cool Whip. Sprinkle 1/2 package frozen coconut on top of cake.
Seal cake in cake hider and place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days before serving (very moist).

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix together. Roll in flour. Cut out with biscuit cutter. Butter top of biscuit and pan. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barcelona beef stew
directions: Cube steak into 1-inch squares.
Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Brown steak in bacon drippings until brown.
Add salt and pepper; put in bacon dish. Saute onions 5 minutes; add to meat.
In the remaining fat, brown rice, then put aside.
Add bay leaf, thyme and garlic to meat.
Add liquid.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cook rice and put in dish with meat.
Add tomatoes and cook 90 minutes.
Serves 6

title: sour sauce for meats
directions: Mix flour and water together.
Add to remaining ingredients and pour over browned meat.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in soup and cheese.
Add broccoli and rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Stir together the egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Quickly stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Add walnuts.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed lasagna noodles
directions: Cut sausage into 4 inch slices. Slit sausage and stuff with cheese. Wrap in cooked lasagna noodles. Put into casserole pan or cake pan. Pour Prego over and bake covered at 350°, about 1 hour.

title: butter pecan bread
directions: Sift
together
flour,
baking
powder,
soda,
salt and spices; stir in sugar and nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture, stirring only until moistened.
Bake in a greased 9 x
5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350°for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool
slightly before removing from pan.
Very good when spread with cream cheese.

title: micro chocolate sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients in Pyrex (quart).
Stir in water; cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and turn on 30 seconds.
Blend in butter and cook 30 seconds longer.
Add vanilla.
If too thin, cook about 10 seconds longer.

title: combination sandwiches(italiano)
directions: Spread mustard on bread.
Combine cheese; place on bottom half of bread.
Arrange meat on both halves.
Spread mayonnaise on 1 half of bread.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Cut into squares and serve immediately.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: apricot balls
directions: Grind apricots.
Add milk and coconut.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until firm.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Place on cookie sheet and let stand until dry.
Store in airtight container in cool place.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch, Jell-O and red food coloring.
Mix until smooth.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add strawberries.
Pour in pie shells and refrigerate.
Garnish with whipped topping when ready to serve.

title: chocolate refrigerator pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix all remaining ingredients except vanilla. Add milk slowly.
Cook over medium heat until it boils.
Cool. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute garlic, onion and green pepper. Put everything into crock and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high 5 to 6 hours.

title: `tis the season pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly mix pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool before serving.
Trim with walnut halves if desired.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Wash cranberries; cut unpeeled oranges into quarters and remove seeds.
Put oranges and cranberries through food grinder or processor.
Stir in sugar.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 4 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients then pour in melted butter and eggs. Mix well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: orange snow balls
directions: Mix all together until well blended.
Roll into marble-size balls.
Roll in more powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator as may be frozen for later use.
Requires no baking.
Makes 3 dozen balls.

title: barbecued short ribs (baked)
directions: Brown ribs in 1 teaspoon vegetable oil in large skillet with onion.
Combine rest of ingredients in covered casserole dish. Add meat and onion; cover and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a preheated 350° oven.

title: marguerite's egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are blended.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and flavorings.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Pour into pastry-lined 10-inch pie pan and bake at 400° until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Add seasoning salt and mix well.
Toss thin potatoes in mixture.
Top with cheese.
Top with Italian seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 25 minutes, or until rice is cooked.

title: zucchini mexicana #2(main dish casserole)
directions: Crumble and brown beef in large skillet or wok.
Add all ingredients, except rice.
Before serving, add rice and blend well. Cheese may be added if desired.
Can be prepared ahead of time and put in casserole.
Add grated cheese topping and bake until heated. Very popular at potlucks.

title: carrot, zucchini and apple muffins
directions: Grease 1/2 cup muffin cups.
Mix all ingredients except eggs and oil in large bowl.
Beat eggs and oil in another bowl to blend.
Stir egg and oil mixture into flour mixture.
Spoon 1/4 cup batter into each muffin cup.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in skillet and saute mushrooms and onion. Blend in flour until smooth.
Add broth and cream, stirring until smooth.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Stir until cheese melts.
Lower heat and simmer uncovered 10 to 15 minutes. While sauce is simmering, cook spaghetti and drain.
Add the spaghetti and ham to the sauce.
Spoon into a greased casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemony cauliflower
directions: Arrange cauliflower in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 5 to 6 minutes or until crisp-tender. Transfer to a serving platter. Keep warm.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion and green pepper in butter for 3 minutes.
Add lean ground chuck and brown meat, breaking up meat as it cooks.
Add seasoning salt, garlic salt and pepper with sugar.
Stir in whole tomatoes and tomato sauce and water.
Heat mixture to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer tomato-meat mixture and uncooked wide noodles.
Top with Mozzarella slices.
Make sure noodles are well covered by sauce.
Cover pan with foil and bake in preheated (350°) oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine juices and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Just before serving, add orange soda, liqueur and ice. Garnish with orange slices, cloves and cherries.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix in large bowl with hands, all ingredients.
Roll in sections for each pie.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix together flour, margarine, and pecans. Pat in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool. Cream together cream cheese, sugar, and 1/2 cup Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Spread blueberry pie filling over cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Thaw raspberries.
Save juice.
Whip cranberry sauce with a hand mixer in a large bowl.
Add sour cream.
Add raspberries while still beating.
Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: six week raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend together; do not overstir.
Keep in refrigerator, covered, and use as needed.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes. Yields 60 muffins.

title: mandarin orange dessert salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add sherbet.
Mix well.
Add well-drained mandarin orange sections.
When mixture is cool but not set, fold in whipped cream.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 225° for 4 hours in 2-inch rolls.
Turn 2 or 3 times.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Mix and put into casserole.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: harvey house slaw
directions: Coarsely chop cabbage into large pot with cover.
Layer on top sliced onions and chopped green pepper.
Pour sugar over vegetables.
Do not stir!
Bring remaining ingredients to a full rolling boil.
Pour over vegetables and sugar.
Cover quickly to keep in steam.
Do not stir for 4 hours.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.
Stays crisp.

title: cucumber and onion with vinegar dressing
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper. Pour over cucumber.

title: corn-y cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; blend in oil, sour cream and corn.
Add cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Bake in 8-inch pan, greased or sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating, for 45 minutes at 375°.
Freezes well.

title: cheerio treats
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Microwave margarine on High 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows; toss until coated.
Microwave 1 minute and 30 seconds on High or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately stir in cereal.
Mix until well coated.
Press mixture into pan using greased spatula or wax paper.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Makes about 24.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix together well and put in loaf pan.
Place maraschino cherries on top of cake mix.
Place half of the nuts in between cherries on top of cake before baking.
Bake at 225° for 2 hours or until done.

title: west texas cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Combine meal, baking powder and cheese.
In another bowl, mix eggs, oil, corn and sour cream.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients.
Spoon into pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Let stand on wire rack 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook sugar, flour, salt, milk and eggs in a heavy saucepan. Use electric mixer while cooking.
When mixture thickens, layer with bananas and wafers.

title: curried zucchini
directions: In a large skillet, saute garlic and onion in olive oil.
Add seasonings.
Stir in zucchini; cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes.
Heat and serve.
Serves 8.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Stir together butter, sugar, syrup, eggs and vanilla. Stir in pecans and pour into shell and bake for 55 minutes.

title: meme's chocolate cake
directions: Heat chocolate, water and shortening until melted and glossy when beaten.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients in order listed.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk; beat 2 minutes.
(Batter is very thin.)
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Of course baking time depends on the size of the pan.)

title: family goulash
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef and drain.
Add celery, onions, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Stir.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 to 50 minutes.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Heat 1 cup of milk and butter; dissolve sugar, cocoa and salt in remaining 1/2 cup of milk.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Pour this mixture into hot milk and butter and cook until stiff, using double boiler or if open pan is used, stir constantly.
Line deep pie tin with rich crust; pricking with fork and bake until a delicate brown.
Put cocoa filling in crust and frost with whites of eggs, well beaten.
Sweeten and flavor to taste.
Put in oven until slightly brown.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat until lemon colored.
Whip the sour cream and fold it into the egg mixture.
Stir in raisins, salt and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350°.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: mrs. jessee's sweet potatoes
directions: Pour off liquid from yams, reserve.
Place yams in glass pan in a single layer.
Butter each yam individually.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: luann's strawberry dessert
directions: Arrange 1/2 of angel food cake, torn in pieces, in a 9 x 13 pan. Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water (no cold water added). Let jello cool and slightly thicken. Stir in strawberries. Fold in egg whites, beaten to meringue consistency and add in container of Cool Whip. Pour mixture over cake and refrigerate until served. Makes 8 to 10 servings, depending on serving size. Great light dessert.

title: rocky mountain potato chowder(delicious)
directions: In heavy stew pot over medium heat, brown bacon; drain.
Add most of onions (reserve green parts for top of soup when finished).
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add broth and potatoes; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add carrots; cook 5 minutes.
Add rest of vegetables.
Add turkey.
Mix milk with cornstarch; add to pot. Bring to boil, stirring constantly about 1 minute, until soup slightly thickens.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 8. Decorate and slightly stir in minced green onion parts before stirring.
Enjoy with cornbread or crackers.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Drain the red kidney beans, butter beans and green beans. Brown the bacon and hamburg.
Drain. Add onions and brown.
Add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream sundae dessert
directions: In a bowl, mix cookie crumbs and butter. Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Carefully spread ice cream over crust. Spread whipped topping over ice cream. Drizzle syrup on top; sprinkle nuts. Freeze until firm (about 2 to 4 hours). Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: easiest green beans
directions: Combine all together and cook on low for 2 - 1/2 hours.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until transparent.
Add vegetable mixture to combine bread crumbs and seasoning.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into your favorite bird.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Add enough water to beet juice to make one cup.

title: company chicken
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch dish with beef.
Put one slice of beef in each chicken piece and wrap in bacon.
Place on beef lining. Blend sour cream, soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 3 hours.

title: caramel layer squares
directions: Place 1/3 cup condensed milk and caramels in a saucepan.
Melt slowly stirring occasionally.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool cookies 1 minute.
Remove.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Sprinkle the salt over the cucumbers and onions; let set for 1 hour.
Combine the last 6 ingredients; pour over cucumbers and onions.
Bring to a boil and put in jars.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, pork, onion, salt, pepper, oregano and thyme with tomato paste.
Put into loaf pan.
Make a trench in the top of meat loaf.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Mix Ricotta cheese and egg; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Remove meat loaf when done and pour cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with chopped onion and tomato.
Bake for 30 additional minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: slush
directions: Mix and freeze for 24 hours.
Then stir and freeze overnight. Fill glass 3/4 full with slush; rest with 7-Up.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half and boil 5 minutes.
Drain and place in baking pan.
Brown meat; drain and add chopped onion, red pepper, stewed tomatoes, salt and cooked rice.
Stuff mixture in bell peppers.
Melt butter; add flour and milk.
Heat until thick.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Pour over peppers.
Cover with foil and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Brown chicken breasts in olive oil.
Lay in casserole dish; top with Italian style tomato sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Continue baking until cheese has melted.
Serve with buttered pasta of any kind.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: potted shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp in saucepan of boiling water until cooked thoroughly (about 3 minutes). Transfer shrimp to bowl of ice water and cool.
Peel and devein shrimp, reserving shells. Finely chop shrimp.
Place in bowl. Cover and refrigerate.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in medium skillet over medium heat. Add shallots; stir 2 minutes. Add shrimp shells; stir 1 minute. Add wine and simmer for 3 minutes.
Increase heat to high.
Add 3 cups water and boil until liquid is reduced to 1 1/2 cups or for about 8 minutes. Strain; discard all solids.
Return cooking liquid to skillet and boil until reduced to 3 tablespoons or for about 10 minutes. Cool.
Beat the cream cheese, tarragon, lemon peel, nutmeg, reduced shrimp liquid and 3 tablespoons butter in a bowl until smooth.
Stir in chopped shrimp.
Season with salt and pepper. Spoon into 2 cup dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pineapple-cheese bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir undrained pineapple into melted butter and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir quickly until all is moistened.
Mix in cheese.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand overnight and eat next day.

title: vegetable quiche(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 20 to 25 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs thoroughly and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat next 3 ingredients until smooth and spread gently over batter in pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Topping will become firmer as cake cools.

title: apple walnut squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add the egg. Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and cinnamon; gradually add to the creamed mixture, beating just until combined. Stir in the apple and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 8-inch pan. Bake for 35-40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: mexican breakfast
directions: Fry sausage and drain grease; let cool.
In a bowl, mix the eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Lightly grease bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with croutons.
Pour over egg mixture.
Cover the top with cheese; crumble sausage on top. Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken until done.
Cook broccoli in salted water and drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and breadcrumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve over prepared rice. Serves 6.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Cook about 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole(side dish)
directions: Mix broccoli, mushroom soup, milk and cheese.
Put in casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Add onions on top of casserole and bake covered 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple, thawed berries and mashed pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold sprayed with nonstick spray.
When set, spread sour cream on top.
Pour on remaining mixture.
Chill until set.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cut in half for family of four.

title: cherry chip cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, Dream Whip and egg.
Form dough into balls.
Dip balls in powdered sugar and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cookie sheet lemon pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar until crumbly.
Press mixture in large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together.
Stir into other ingredients.
Serve cold.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender in salted water.
Drain.
Cool slightly.
Toss in butter and pepper.
Spoon half of the potato mixture into lightly greased 3 qt. casserole dish.
Top with layer of bacon pieces and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until cheese if bubbly.

title: conch stew
directions: Add salad oil to pot.
Place tomato and minced ingredients in pot.
Cook lightly.
Add conch, chili powder and seasonings to taste.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: date-nut loaf
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Dredge nuts and dates with cup of sifted flour.
Fold into egg mixture. Add salt.
Bake in loaf pans at 300° until done.

title: chicken paprika
directions: In large skillet, brown lightly salted and peppered chicken in oil and butter.
Saute onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery.
Stir in rice to coat.
Add the chicken stock.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Add mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Stir.
Add chopped stuffed olives.
Cover.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Check to make sure it doesn't dry out.
Remove.
Cover to reduce liquid.
Serve with sour cream.

title: cornmeal chicken
directions: Preheat oil in fryer to 350°.
Mix cornmeal, bread crumbs, herbs and spices in bowl; set aside.
Place chicken in large pan, cover with water, season and bring to a boil.
Skim water and cook, partially covered 20 to 22 minutes over low heat.
Remove chicken from pan and trim skin away.
Dredge chicken with flour and dip into beaten eggs coated with cornmeal.
Deep fry 6 to 7 minutes.

title: mango chutney sausage
directions: Microwave wine, mustard and chutney 3 minutes on High.
Add cooked sausage.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ham appettillas
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator. Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions and olives. Spread thin layer of mixture on tortillas. Arrange 4 slices of ham over cheese.
Tightly roll up tortilla. Wrap individually in plastic wrap. Place in refrigerator at least 3 hours or overnight.
To serve, cut in 3/4-inch slices. Makes about 64 appetizers.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to a rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat for one minute. Remove form heat and beat in all 4 eggs at once.
Continue beating until smooth.
Mixture wil become very thick.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls or heaping tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until puffs are golden. Cool away from draft.
Makes 12 puffs.
Fill with your favorite pudding.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Add sour cream and mushroom soup.
Add cheese. Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix and cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles for 8 minutes.
Saute onions in margarine. Prepare enough instant potatoes to serve 6.
Melt Velveeta cheese. Mix melted cheese into potatoes and spread in bottom of greased pan.
Then layer with noodles and over that pour onion mixture. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, combine egg whites, sugar, syrup and water.
Heat one minute to combine ingredients.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, beating constantly, about 7 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Remove from boiling water, add vanilla and continue beating until thick enough to spread.
Good on spice cakes.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Cook eggplant.
Combine all together remaining ingredients. Spoon into casserole dish.
Sprinkle reserved stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in a large pot and cover with water.
Add onion, carrots, celery, corn and salt.
Boil until chicken is done, approximately 1/2 hour.
Remove chicken and debone it.
Add bouillon cubes to boiling water and dissolve.
Add the deboned chicken to the water.
See recipe for drop noodles.

title: molly's beefy corn pie
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, ketchup, onion, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pat this meat mixture over the bottom and sides of a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Make stuffing with 1 cup water and 1/4 cup butter; set aside. Stir soup, milk and mayonnaise with the chicken.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and pepper; add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add cheese.
In another pan, dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add frozen broccoli; cook until tender.
Add to cheese mixture; blend.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place bottom crust in a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and pour into bottom crust.
Place top crust on and crimp.
Bake at 375° for approximately 55 minutes.
Great to prepare ahead of time and freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice; let stand.
Cook broccoli.
Mix all ingredients, then place in a quart dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a 16 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallow cream over cake while hot.
When cake is cool, top with icing.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Skin chicken.
Put in a covered dish.
Cover with meat tenderizer.
Add the cream soups.
Sprinkle with garlic.
Cover. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Salt to taste.

title: easy crab cakes
directions: In bowl, combine red pepper, green onions, mayonnaise, lemon juice, seasoned salt, garlic powder and cayenne pepper. Stir in Chicken of the Sea crab, egg and 1/3 cup bread crumbs (mixture may be sticky). Divide and form mixture into 4 balls. Roll crab balls in remaining bread crumbs; flatten into cakes about 1/2-inch thick. In skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Fry crab cakes 3 to 4 minutes per side until golden brown. Makes 4 servings. Preparation time: 10 minutes. Cooking time: about 8 minutes.

title: switchel(an old time haying drink)
directions: Put ingredients in a 1/2 gallon glass container. Place in refrigerator to cool and dissolve. A great thirst quencher.
Works even when it isn't kept cold.

title: favorite chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add sugar and water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat 2 minutes more.
Bake at 350° in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer about 15 minutes.
Make layers of Doritos, sliced cheese and meat mixture.
Bake in (350°) moderate oven until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Serve with Doritos and green salad.
tags: cream of chicken with rice soup

title: extra simple roast
directions: Place roast in crock pot. Pour in sourp, broth, dry onion soup mix an desired amount of pepper.
Add enough water to cover most of roast
Cook on LOW for about 8 hours.
Drippings easily thicken for a great gravy.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix with hands the cheese, garlic salt, baking soda and nuts. Mix well.
Makes 6 to 8 logs.

title: spring green dessert
directions: First layer:
Mix flour, oleo and pecans together.
Pat into a 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes -- Do not brown and cool.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Boil chicken and pick off of the bone.
Layer in bottom of baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and broth well and pour over chicken.
Drain the peas and carrots and layer over soup. Mix flour, butter and milk together and pour over the top. Bake for 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In large skillet or electric frypan, melt butter.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender, not brown.
Add chili, corn and salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Top with shredded cheese. Cover; heat on low 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low heat, don't overstir, to a soft ball (until a small amount forms a ball when dropped into a glass of cold water).
Stir in butter, peanut butter and vanilla. Spread into buttered 9-inch pie plate.

title: mexican chicken breasts(low-fat, microwave cooked)
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix cracker crumbs, chili pepper and Parmesan cheese together.
Dip chicken breasts in margarine, then in crumbs.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Remove and turn over; add rest of crumbs on top.
Place 1 serving of cheese on each and 2 tablespoons salsa on each.
Microwave 2 minutes or until center of meat is white.
Serves 2.

title: potato-ham-cheese casserole
directions: Arrange potato slices in 2-quart baking dish; set aside. Combine butter and onion in 2-quart measure.
Microwave 3 minutes on High, or until onion is transparent.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, curry powder, shredded cheese and milk; microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High, or until mixture is hot and cheese is melted.
Stir and add ham.
Pour over potatoes.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes on "6" or until potatoes are heated through.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Layer vegetables, starting with potatoes, then layer carrots, meat, onions, rice, celery and keep in layers.
Pour tomatoes or soup over all.
Season each layer with salt,
pepper and butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers in 1/2 cup margarine, then put grated cheese on top of crackers.
Cook until bubbly hot in 350° oven.

title: pork chops for two
directions: Trim fat and cook to get 2 tablespoons fat.
Discard trimmings.
Brown chops and set aside.
Cook rice and onions until rice is golden, stirring constantly.
Stir in water and bouillon. Bring to boil; stir in chopped apple.
Turn mixture into a 6 1/2 x 6 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerated tortellini salad
directions: Cook the tortellini according to package directions and cool. Combine all ingredients, then fold in sour cream mixture. Refrigerate.
Makes an excellent dish for parties and light meals.

title: spaghetti sauce to can
directions: Peel and dice tomatoes.
Add all ingredients, except tomato paste.
Cook 2 hours.
Add tomato paste.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into scalded jars and seal.
Yields 12 to 14 quarts.

title: perfect pie shell
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until it resembles coarse corn meal.
Sprinkle water, 1 tablespoon at a time, over mixture.
Work lightly with a fork until dough is formed.
Roll thin.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes, depending on oven.

title: velvety chocolate frosting
directions: Add 1/4 cup hot water and the sugar to chocolate and mix well. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Slowly add butter, then vanilla, and beat until smooth.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Mix cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and sugar. Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with chopped pecans and drained, chopped maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Combine
the
first
5	ingredients.
Add
flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Beat well. Coat angel food cake pan with Pam.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or little longer until top of cake is dry.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be used for weddings by multiplying recipe by 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lo-cal pineapple dessert
directions: Put pineapple and cottage cheese in a blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Add instant pudding.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a bowl and fold in Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; make into rolls.
Chill and slice.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40-50 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and melted margarine (and coconut if desired) and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Add buttermilk.
Pour yeast in; mix well.
Add cheese and garlic; mix well.
Sift flour on plastic paper.
Roll out dough and cut.
Dip each biscuit in butter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions; cool and crumble. Toss remaining ingredients together, add to crumbled cornbread and chill.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars, then egg and vanilla.
Blend sifted flour, soda and salt.
Roll cookie dough into individual balls.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

(At Christmas, you can dip rounded balls into colored sugar before placing, sugar side up on cookie sheet.) Press unwrapped Hershey's Kiss in center of cookie, as soon as you remove from oven, then take off cookie sheet.

title: cranberry orange loaf
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder , salt and baking soda.
Cut in shortening until coarse crumbs. Combine egg, relish, nuts, orange juice and water.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan. Stir in milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Remove and set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Gradually stir 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes over medium heat.
Remove; add 3/4 cup coconut, butter and vanilla.
When butter is melted, pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites; add 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Spread over filling; sprinkle 1/4 cup coconut and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except green onions in saucepan. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove 1 cup of mixture; process in blender and return to saucepan.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with green onions.
(If no blender is available, potatoes can be mashed by hand.)
Contains 48 calories per cup.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup hot water. Stir in other ingredients. Pour into a large or individual molds.
Chill overnight or until set.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco or butter.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time.
Add chocolate mixture.
Add alternately flour, buttermilk soda, vanilla and salt.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 cake pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Combine in a casserole with soup, water and rice.
Add soy sauce and salt and pepper. Cover and bake about 1/2 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and add noodles and return to oven for another half hour without cover.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with the graham crackers to make crust.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tortilla chip casserole
directions: Crush tortilla chips to make 1/4 cup.
Set aside.
Saute onion in butter until softened; set aside.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese and cumin in a small bowl.
Place a layer of chips in buttered 9-inch square dish; layer other ingredients, repeat.

title: money's divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water together.
Boil for about 5 minutes.
Pour half of boiled mixture over egg whites.
Return other half to burner.
Boil until it spins a thread when poured out of spoon.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl until smooth.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients until smooth; pour on top. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets with roots and about 2-inches of stem left on, until tender.
Use enough water to cover.
Dip into cold water and peel.
Combine sugar, spices, vinegar and water in a large preserving kettle.
Add beets and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars and cover with boiling hot syrup; seal.

title: grandma's lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a cake pan.
Beat rest of ingredients together until smooth.
Pour crust mix over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour in one can of cherries, peaches or blackberries.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Remove and retain seasoning packet from noodles.
Crush noodles with rolling pin.
Combine noodles, cabbage, scallions, sunflower seeds, and almonds.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; rinse and drain.
Cook beans in water to cover until tender; add onions, celery, parsley and oregano. Dilute soup according to can directions and add to pot.
Add potatoes and carrots; cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook kielbasa; drain fat and add to pot.
Heat through. Freezes very well.

title: berry quick dessert
directions: Put berries in casserole large enough to hold plus some room for biscuit topping.
Mix berries and sugar together; put in casserole.
Cover with biscuits, your own or Bisquick. Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes (whenever biscuits are done).

title: my aunt carol's kugel
directions: Beat the eggs and add all the ingredients, except noodles. Cook noodles 5 minutes.
Add ingredients to noodles.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 of an hour.
May take slightly longer.

title: broccoli and corn scallop
directions: Cook and stir onion in 1 tablespoon of butter in medium saucepan on medium heat. Blend in flour. Gradually add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add cheese. Stir until melted. Stir in corn and 1/4 cup of the crumbs. Arrange broccoli in a 12 x 8 dish. Top with sauce. Mix remaining 1/4 cup of crumbs and 1 tablespoon of butter. Sprinkle over sauce in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cool cake
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.
Cover with lemon pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pretzel snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dressing mix, garlic powder and oil.
Dip pretzels into the mixture and lay on a cookie sheet. Bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir; dump pretzels in a plastic bag and shake.
Pretzels may be served whole or broken in smaller pieces.
Bet you can't eat just one.

title: hummingbird bars
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy tuna turnovers
directions: Fill each biscuit with mixture; fold over and seal.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (optional).

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice.
Add water.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Spoon cream of chicken soup over chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Cut off stems and finely chop.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese, chopped stems and parsley.
Fill each mushroom cap with mixture.
Drizzle with oil.
Add 1/8 to 1/4-inch of water in bottom of pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian cioppino
directions: Mix all ingredients listed, except fish, in a saucepan. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: nellie's yellow rice
directions: Heat oil in medium saucepan, add onions and saute until nearly tender.
Add saffron and continue to saute until onions are done.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add rice, reduce heat and cover and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid has been absorbed.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add flour and make into paste.
In bowl, mix cocoa, milk and sugar.
Pour into flour and butter. Cook until gravy consistency.
If too thick, add more milk.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, if desired.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: pumpkin bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
With electric mixer, add other ingredients.
Divide batter equally into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done (clean pick).
Freezes very well.

title: spiced cider(8 punch cup servings)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Cool.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours, then strain. Serve cold or reheat.
Garnish each mug with a lemon slice.

title: poodle cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler pot.
Combine noodles and nuts in bowl.
Pour chocolate over noodle mixture; stir to mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper; cool.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft.
Beat in peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Blend in Cool Whip and freeze.
Eat and enjoy.

title: spiced biscotti
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Can do by hand or mixer. Flour hands and roll in 12-inch log by 3-inch. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be soft, but that's okay. Cool well. Cut diagonal. Toast both sides under boiler if want crispy.
Can frost one end with melted chocolate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare raw apples and set aside.
Measure salad oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy on low speed.
Sift flour.
Sift again and add salt, soda and baking powder.
Add a small amount of flour mixture at a time to the creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
When all flour has been added, fold in chopped pecans and apples.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Add crumbled Ritz crackers on top for last 10 minutes.

title: aunt maxine's orange salad
directions: Drain fruit, saving 1/2 cup juice.
Mix juice with pie filling.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: toasted peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut bread slices into 5 sticks.
Place on cookie sheet.
Toast in preheated 250° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Mix peanut butter and oil in top of double boiler and heat, stirring until well blended.
Dip sticks into mixture and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Let cool on wax paper.
Store, tightly covered.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: ranch mashed potatoes
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add dressing mix to potatoes; stir well.
Add butter to taste.

title: j c's salmon filet mignon
directions: Rinse steaks in cold water; pound slightly.
Butterfly each steak (cut in half, leaving a "hinge" on one side of each). Sprinkle garlic salt on each inside cavity.

title: strawberry slush fruit
directions: Bring to boil first 2 ingredients.
Beat with mixer bananas and strawberries.
Pour over fruit.
Add ingredients to sugar and freeze to slush.
Serve by mixing with 7-Up, about 1 to 1.
Yields about 1 gallon.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Place pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix 1 German chocolate cake mix according to directions and pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt oleo and combine with cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Add carrots by hand.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: easy barbecups
directions: Brown beef, stirring to crumble; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and onion; stir well and set aside.
Separate biscuits and place each in muffin cups, pressing up sides.
Spoon meat mixture evenly into biscuit cups.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400 degrees for 8 minutes.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Fill 4-cup container with evaporated milk and complete filling to top with water.
Add vanilla and sugar and freeze.
Add well-mashed fruit, if desired.

title: pralines
directions: In a deep heavy saucepan, stir buttermilk, soda, sugar, and salt together.
Stir over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mahogany in color (does not quite get to soft-ball stage).
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Let cool until you can comfortably put hand on outside of pan.
Beat with spoon until almost thick.
Add nuts, and drop by spoonfuls on marble slab or wax paper.

title: pot roast in casserole
directions: Pour mixture over top of roast then slice onion rings on top. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: orange-pineapple torte cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges well.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch layer pans at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift in flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts and stir in mashed bananas.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan(s) and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: mock pie
directions: Crush crackers and add 1/2 cup sugar and pecans. Beat egg whites and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in pie plate and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Place half of the stuffing mix in 2-quart baking dish.
Top with half of the broccoli, then chicken. Top chicken with remaining broccoli and then stuffing mix. Spoon can of chicken soup over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Take pineapple and 1 cup of the sugar; bring to a boil. Remove from fire.
Add the orange jello mix to the mixture; let cool.
Add the buttermilk, the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Stir and then refrigerate.

title: kerry's favorite cheese "bones"
directions: In large bowl, pour hot water over oatmeal and margarine; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in powdered milk, grated cheese, salt and egg.
Add cornmeal and wheat germ; mix well.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well after each.
Knead 3 or 4 minutes, adding more flour if necessary, to make a stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into shapes.
Place on greased sheet and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Turn off heat and leave in oven for 1 1/2 hours or longer.

title: lizzies (fruit cookies)
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients; make batter as for cake.
Then add pecans, raisins, cherries and pineapple.
Stir until fruit and nuts are coated good.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake in slow oven (300°) about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Flavor is better if kept 2 to 3 weeks before serving (that is, if you can keep them hidden from Daddy, Bill, Ron and Sue!).

title: cheese ball
directions: Make in large ball and chill.

title: partin valley fried catfish
directions: Starting at rib cage
of
catfish,
cut
3 large X's on each side of fish.
Sprinkle
with
salt;
place
in a shallow dish and add
Tabasco sauce.
Marinate in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Place
cornmeal,
flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a plastic bag;
drop catfish in, one at a time, and shake until
completely coated.
Fry in deep hot oil (375°) until fish float
to
the
top
and are a golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: picante chicken
directions: Piece chicken in a greased baking dish.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thick. Cut with cookie cutters.
Place onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: connie's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and coat pasta.
Chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until just cooked through.
Drain.
Cool. Peel skins off and cut into 1/2-inch thick circles.
On a greased griddle, fry until lightly brown on both sides.
Serve with brown sugar and butter if desired.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over low heat until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.
Cool.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions on package; fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Mix in all other ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting every now and then.

title: chicken milanese
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper, garlic salt and flour. Shake to remove excess.
Dip in egg; coat with bread crumbs.
Cook for approximately 7 minutes on each side in the margarine/shortening mixture in a skillet.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Put pineapple juice in 2-cup measuring container.
Add water to make 1 1/4 cups.
In pan, combine sugar, cornstarch, juice, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil and cook for 4 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with pineapple and green pepper slices and bake for 30 minutes more or until chicken is tender.

title: fudgy butterscotch bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, condensed milk and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Heat, stirring constantly, in a double boiler, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Set aside.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except oil.
Heat oil in skillet.
Form mixture into patties and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Makes approximately 6 cakes.

title: sarah's pecan chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add tomato sauces; stir well.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour or more.
You may use the amount of each ingredient that you desire to suit your taste.

title: aunt calla's casserole
directions: Brown pork.
Add onions and celery.
Saute until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sausage egg bake
directions: Brown sausage in skillet 3 to 4 minutes. Drain fat and cool. In large bowl, beat eggs and milk. Add mustard, salt, pepper and bread cubes; mix well. Fold in cooked sausage and cheese. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mock apricot jam
directions: Simmer zucchini for 10 minutes.
Add sugar, lemon juice, pineapple and gelatin.
Continue to cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: golden rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2-inch pieces.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and flour to eggs.
Combine with rhubarb.
Stir in orange juice and rind.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Bone it.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place chicken into 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cube and boil potatoes with salt until tender.
Mash potatoes and add next 4 ingredients.
Add milk alternately.
May not need whole can; potatoes should not be runny.
Pour in casserole dish. Top with cheese and Potato Toppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (Good left over.)

title: monkey cake
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll in granulated sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place evenly in pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Refrigerate overnight (optional). Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Add chopped nuts before baking is desired.

title: peanut butter puffs
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
Adding sugar very gradually, beat until stiff peaks form.
Beat peanut butter to soften; fold thoroughly into meringue.
Drop from teaspoon 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then peel and dice apples and add to mixture or slice and dip apples into mixture.
Fry in hot oil. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.

title: ham cream cheese spread
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, sour cream and garlic powder until smooth.
Stir in ham and onions.
Serve with bagels.

title: raspberry jello salad(good, easy and quick)
directions: Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pork chop and corn skillet
directions: Brown pork chops slowly and evenly in hot skillet.
Add the hot water, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover; simmer for about 40 minutes.
Remove chops from skillet.
Add corn; sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Arrange chops on top of corn; crown each chop with a tablespoon of chili sauce and a dill pickle slice. Cover skillet; continue cooking for about 10 minutes, until corn is heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dottie's christmas gems
directions: Use miniature muffin pan.

title: persimmon pie
directions: Mix persimmon pulp, egg and milk.
Mix
sugar, salt and cornstarch. Add to first mixture.
Pour filling in pastry shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 50 to 60 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip egg whites and add 6 level tablespoons of sugar while beating.
Place mixture in refrigerator until rest of cake is mixed.
Cream butter and gradually add rest of sugar.
Add egg yolks, two at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Whip until mixture is as light as possible (use low speed on mixer).
At low speed, whip in egg white mixture only long enough to mix well.
Bake 1 hour 25 minutes at 300°.
Use a 10 x 4-inch deep pan.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt; let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine with remaining ingredients; cook for 30 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars; seal and process 10 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove and add onion and celery.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add sugar, vinegar and water; stir with a whisk.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Add parsley, celery seed and bacon. Remove from heat.
Place potatoes in dish sprayed with vegetable spray.
Pour dressing over all, being careful not to break the potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit in butter, then in sugar mixture.
Place close together on a cookie sheet or overlap in a pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix corn and syrup in large roaster.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
After removing from oven, toss corn with large spoon 5 to 10 minutes to prevent sticking together.

title: quick salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 2 tablespoons liquid.
In a mixing bowl, combine salmon, egg and onion; stir in flour.
Combine baking powder and the reserved liquid.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form in small patties; shallow fry in hot Crisco until golden, about 5 minutes.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: honey-orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the eggs with 2 teaspoons water. In another bowl, mix the breadcrumbs with spices.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in breadcrumbs.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken on all sides.
Combine 1/4 cup honey, hot water and orange juice.
Place chicken in casserole; pour in water, honey/orange juice mixture.
Add ginger.
Cover and simmer in oven for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: scalloped corn
directions: If using fresh corn, prepare and cook ears; cut enough kernels from ears to measure 2 cups.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook sausage in Dutch oven until browned.
Remove; drain.
Add oil to drippings in Dutch oven.
Add celery, green pepper, parsley and garlic; saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, broth and onions.
Stir in seasonings and bay leaf.
Add rice and sausage; mix well.
Bring to boil, reduce flame to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn off flame, add shrimp and turn mixture into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Remove bay leaf; discard.

title: creamy seafood casserole
directions: Combine Neufchatel cheese and the next 6 ingredients.
Coat a 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
Place 1/2 of macaroni in baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 crabmeat over macaroni.
Spoon 1/2 of cheese mixture over crabmeat.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded Monterey Jack cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and water; let stand 10 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in cereal mixture.

title: peanut butter chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in the egg, butter and milk, just until blended.
Fold in peanut butter chips. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: fresh cherry pie
directions: Mix together and bake in pastry shell at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy lemon cheesecake bars
directions: Crust:
In medium bowl, combine flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until small crumbs form.
Press lightly into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: baked chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in 2 quarts of salted water until tender; remove from broth.
Debone and cut into bite size serving pieces.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt together oleo and cocoa.
Add the sugar and milk; boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the oatmeal, vanilla flavor, and coconut or nuts.
Drop onto waxed paper; let cool. Yields about 36 cookies.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine, add cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake at
350° for 30 to 35 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: For Decoration:
Make 3 cups cooked ziti pasta and garnish with parsley and 1 teaspoon olive oil.

title: plum cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add to butter mixture. Spread mixture into the bottom of a spring-form pan.
Place plum halves skin side up evenly around on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with a little sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the hamburg.
Precook the vegetables.
Line a casserole dish, coated with butter or margarine, with layer of mashed potatoes, a layer of the ground and browned beef, then a layer of the prepared carrots.
Repeat these layers (potatoes, beef and carrots).
Cover with remaining mashed potatoes.
Dot with bits of butter or margarine.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°, enough to heat it through.

title: thank you dessert
directions: Fold all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate at least two hours before cutting into serving pieces.

title: oriental mushrooms
directions: In a large skillet cook and stir onions in butter until tender. Stir in mushrooms.
Sprinkle flour over mixture until mushrooms are coated.
Add water, bouillon and soy sauce until bouillon is absorbed.
Cook over medium heat about 3 minutes.

title: crawdads (crayfish)
directions: Mix it all together and dip your crawdad meat in it.
Eat your fill.

title: casserole for the crowd
directions: Brown meat, add onion and cook until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add next 8 ingredients, mix well and stir in noodles. Pour into casserole and sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Add sauce to ground beef mixture and peppers and onions. Place in greased casserole.
Layer tortillas, sauce and cheese until all used.
Pour milk over.
Bake for 45 minutes or until thick at 350°.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Lightly butter a 13X9 baking dish and put in cauliflower. Season with seasoning salt and sprinkle with cheeses.
Beat eggs in half and half and pour over cauliflower.
Top with buttered breadcrumbs.
Bake at 375 degrees until lightly golden brown.

title: pizza crust
directions: Put warm water and yeast in mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes. Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Mix well and add 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add remaining flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Spread out in pizza pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes. Add desired toppings.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes (until cheese is bubbly).

title: pancakes
directions: Mix slightly beaten eggs to shortening and buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour on heated griddle.
If you don't have buttermilk on hand, substitute sour milk instead.
Place 1 tablespoon of vinegar in a 1 cup measuring cup; then fill with milk so as to measure one cup.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Cook the potatoes at noon; drain.
Save water and mash potatoes.
Pour all together; let cool until evening.
Add the cake yeast and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Let stand until morning. Sift flour in dishpan.
Make a hole.
Add sponge, salt, eggs, shortening, 2 scoops sugar and lukewarm water.
Mix into a soft dough; keep warm.
Let raise until double in bulk.

title: creamed carrot soup
directions: In saucepan, combine broth, onion, carrots and seasonings. Bring to a boil; simmer until tender.
In blender, blend cooked mixture until smooth.
In separate saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; stir until thickened.
Add vegetable puree.

title: date cake
directions: Mix dates and soda. Cover with 2 cups boiling water (cool). Cream 2 cups sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla, flour and nuts. Mix this mixture with dates mixture. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line a 13 x 9-inch glass dish with whole graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Add second layer of crackers.
Cover crackers with remaining pudding mixture. Add last layer of crackers.

title: scalloped cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into wedges.
Place in a large pan and cover with water.
Parboil until almost tender.
Lift wedges out of water carefully; arrange in oblong casserole, reserving cabbage juice. Blend butter, flour and salt; add 1 cup reserved juice gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until thick and creamy; add cheeses.
Pour over cabbage wedges; sprinkle with potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: diana's vinegar pie
directions: Beat together well the yolks of eggs, small piece of butter, cornstarch and sugar.
Add to boiling water and cider vinegar. Cook until thick.
Add flavoring.
Place in baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: daddy's favorite blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well; add buttermilk, eggs and butter, which has been melted and browned slightly.
Mix well; fold in blueberries.
Fill well-greased muffin tins half full; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 24 small muffins.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery in oil; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 30 minutes or longer (flavor improves with longer cooking time).

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer in a large soup pan for 3 hours.
When meat is tender, use a slotted spoon to shred meat against side of pan.
Continue to simmer until barbecue is the right consistency to be served on hamburger rolls.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, 3/4 cup brown sugar substitute, milk, egg, melted margarine and vanilla, stirring until well blended. Spoon into a shallow baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray (Pam).
Combine flour and remaining 1/4 cup brown sugar substitute; cut in 1 tablespoon margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over potatoes and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serving amount is 1/3 cup at 85 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 starch.

title: cabbage and shrimp salad
directions: Measure all ingredients, except cabbage and shrimp in bowl and mix well.
Shred cabbage and drain shrimp. Put in large bowl and pour dressing over.
Mix well.

title: cinnamon spiral bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a mixing bowl.
Stir in milk, oats, brown sugar, shortening, salt, raisins and half the flour. Mix with a spoon until smooth.
Add rest of flour and mix with hands.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Round up in a greased bowl; bring greased side up.
Let rise until double in a warm place (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Divide dough into 2 parts and shape into balls.
Roll each into a 15 x 8-inch oblong.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon, setting aside 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Roll up like jelly roll, sealing tightly at ends.

title: rosave's famous dip
directions: Add enough cream to cream cheese to make creamy.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: veggie dip
directions: Put in blender and serve chilled with veggies.

title: crispy potato wedges(low-fat)
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl; add cold water to cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a nonstick baking sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan; set aside.
Combine all ingredients except mini chips chocolates and walnuts in large mixer bowl; blend well on medium speed.
Stir in mini chips chocolates and walnuts.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill deep dish pie pan with sliced apples.
Pour water over apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Mix last 3 ingredients together with pastry blender and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease one 9-inch spring-form pan.

Dust with graham cracker crumbs. Sieve the cottage cheese into a large mixing bowl. Add the cream cheese. Beat with high speed of electric mixer until creamy. Beating at high speed, blend in sugar, then eggs. Reduce speed to low. Add cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until blended. Add melted margarine and sour cream.
Blend on low speed. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325°
(slow) oven about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm around edges. Turn off oven.
Let stand in oven 2 hours. Remove and cool completely on wire rack. Chill and remove sides of pan.
May be frozen.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all, except pecans, chill and form in a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with Wheat Thins or buttery crackers.

title: jack's crab quarters
directions: In medium saucepan over moderate heat, melt butter.
Add the next 5 ingredients and mix into a thick paste.
Spread over English muffin halves.
Place on cookie sheet.
Freeze for 1 hour. Cut halves into quarters.
Broil until topping bubbles.
(Also can be put in freezer bags for later use.) Serve hot.

title: heaven bound waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add milk, oil and egg. Combine until almost smooth with only a few small lumps. Cook and enjoy!

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in 2 cups of water for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, but only half of flour, plus the 1 cup cold water.
Add remaining flour.
Beat with mixer.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan 1 hour at 350°.
Test for doneness at 50 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
(Delicious with butter spread on it.)

title: deluxe rolls
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
After 5 minutes, stir and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add about half of the flour.
Add the beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Mix thoroughly.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain off grease. In a large pot, combine all ingredients and seasonings to taste. Serve on a bed of rice.

title: white cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add extract and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Chill pie shell while making filling.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Gradually stir in scalded milk. Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 to 30 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center of custard comes out clean.
Cool on cooling rack 15 to 30 minutes, then chill in refrigerator.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Pour peaches on top of melted butter. Mix other ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sensational salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a quart jar; shake.
Dressing will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: norwegian kringles
directions: Mix sugar and cream. Scald and cool.
Blend all ingredients. Add sufficient flour to knead until quite firm.
Let rise until double in bulk and knead again.
Let rise again.
On a board, flatten to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut 1/2-inch strips 6 inches long. Roll dough between hands to rope shape and form a figure 8.
Dip one side in melted butter and then in sugar and put on a lightly greased cookie sheet with sugar side up.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Place the oil, vinegar, lemon juice, garlic, mustard and herbs in a screw-top jar or small mixing bowl.
Season with salt and pepper and shake or whisk together thoroughly.
Makes about 1 cup. This dressing is good on Tossed Greek Salad.

title: scampi shrimp microwave
directions: In glass casserole, cook butter on high for 2 minutes or until melted.
Add garlic.
Cook on high for
2 minutes.
Mix in cheese, parsley, lemon juice and shrimp.
Cook on high for 2-1/2 minutes or until shrimp is cooked.

title: sunny morning brunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, sour cream, eggs, oil, water and almond extract; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Generously grease a 10-inch tube pan; sprinkle coconut and almonds in pan, then top with 1/3 jar preserves.
Pour in half of cake batter, dot with remaining preserves and cover with rest of cake batter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes (cake is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean).
Cool 30 minutes, then invert on serving dish.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend well with fork.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bread pudding with vanilla or lemon sauce
