directions: Place bread in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Mix the hot water and brown sugar in a bowl.
Pour over the bread.
Combine the eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and salt in a bowl and mix well.
Pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Drizzle with vanilla or lemon sauce.

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Boil sugar and Karo syrup; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir in.
Add Rice Krispies and stir.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased pan and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits in double boiler; spread evenly over Rice Krispies.
Refrigerate until set, then cut into 48 pieces.

title: county bean salad
directions: Beat oil, vinegar, lemon juice and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk or fork until thoroughly blended.
Add chickpeas, kidney beans, black beans, chopped onion and parsley; toss well to mix.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Scramble in butter.
Put eggs in shallow casserole; spread soup, mushrooms and cheese.
Sprinkle bacon all over top evenly.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue mix for chicken
directions: Mix all together with whisk real good.
Baste chicken and grill or fry.

title: gail's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
If sauce is too thick, add water.
Spoon over your favorite meat.
Bake and enjoy.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: crunchy beef bake casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except onions. Pour half the mixture into a 2-quart casserole, sprayed with Pam or greased lightly with margarine.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Pour remaining mixture over onions; cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Thaw fish enough to separate.
Arrange on buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with pepper and dot with margarine.
Spread shrimp soup over fillets; sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: reduced fat chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, mixed vegetables and cream of chicken soup in a medium bowl.
Place 1 pie crust into pie baking dish.
Trim excess crust even with pan edge.
Add filling.
Top with second crust.
Press firmly along edge to hold crust when trimming.
Trim top crust even with bottom crust.
Flute edge.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until pie crust is golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and add enough water to make a stiff dough.
Shape into patties and fry in deep fat in a heavy frying pan until golden brown.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Heat water and in it melt margarine.
Add stuffing.
Mix and toss with fork until it's moist.
Save out a little gravy (1/3 can); mix remainder with chicken.
Cover bottom of large casserole with half of stuffing mixture.
Add the chicken and gravy mixture. Cover with remaining stuffing.
Dribble remaining gravy on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans. Combine ingredients.
Pour into cake pans.
Bake 15 minutes. Cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix beans together and add 1/2 package taco seasoning.
Add jar of taco sauce and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Heat through for 10 minutes.
Saute pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Add to pan.
Add crushed corn chips.
Put over lettuce.
Add remaining cheese and add additional taco sauce (if desired).

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with salt.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes until tender. Cube potatoes; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix with dressing, mayonnaise, celery and eggs.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs. Add butter and milk. Add vanilla and coconut. Pour into deep dish shell. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. To make brown crust top, dash about 1 Tbsp meal and maybe an egg.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, egg, crumbs, onion, salt, oregano, pepper and 1/3 can tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Shape into flat rectangle about 8
x 12-inches on waxed paper.
Pat or roll to even thickness, about 1/2 inch.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over meat; roll up like jelly roll, pressing ends to seal.
Place roll in 9
x
12-inch glass baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce mixed
with Italian
seasoning
over
top.
Cover
with waxed paper; microwave
to
minutes
on High.
Let stand at least
10 minutes before serving.
Conventional method:
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart bowl.
Cover and microwave, approximately 15 minutes, stirring twice.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Saute onion and green peppers in oil until tender.
Salt and pepper pork chops.
Brown pork chops in oil.
Add tomatoes and simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: elegant scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin and oil; stir well.
Sift flour and add to sugar mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: cheese and sausage roll-ups
directions: Cook and drain sausage links.
Trim crust from bread.
Press each bread slice down with hand.
Mix cheese and butter together. Spread on both sides of each bread slice.
Roll a sausage link in each slice.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tuna melt surprise
directions: Drain the tuna; put into bowl and add mayonnaise, mixing until everything is smooth.
Put bread slices on a cookie sheet in the oven at 400°, then put tuna mixture on top.
Carefully make a nice decoration with the alfalfa sprouts and cook for 10 minutes. Makes enough for you and two friends.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 2 cups crumbled bread crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt one stick of margarine and pour over crumbs. Place cooked chicken pieces over crumbs.
Mix sour cream, onion, soup, pepper, sage and celery.
Pour over chicken.
Put 2 remaining cups of bread crumbs on top of chicken.
Pour chicken broth slowly over bread and chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour, longer if needed.
Top should be slightly brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer asparagus, then add layer of soup, layer of egg and layer of potato chips.
Sprinkle pimento throughout.
Do two of these layers.
Top with crushed potato chips or bread crumbs or crushed Ritz crackers, then a final topping of grated cheese.
Bake on low for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Line bottom and sides of baking dish with hamburger.
Put layer of chopped onion and chopped mango (green pepper) and layer of cheese.
Pour can of cream of mushroom soup over cheese, then top with Tater Tots.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, about an hour.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Have all ingredients room temperature.
Melt margarine and set aside to cool.
Place both cheeses in large mixing bowl and beat at high speed.
Gradually beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour and cornstarch; add to mixture.
Add cooled margarine and sour cream.
Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Cake should be light brown.
Turn off oven.
Let cake sit in oven 2 hours.
Remove from oven and cool 2 hours.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Remove sides of pan and cover.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking
powder
and milk.
Spoon over melted margarine. Top with fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cinnamon loaf
directions: Scald
milk;
add
oleo,
1/4 cup sugar, salt and stir. Cool to lukewarm.
Measure water and add yeast.	Stir.
Add to milk and stir
in egg, then flour, cup by cup.
Knead and put in bowl. Let
raise.
Divide
into
loaves,
roll
out and spread with 1/2
cup
sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll up and put in bread
pan and let rise.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting while still warm.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix orange jello, tapioca pudding and vanilla pudding all together with cold water.
Cook until thick at a full, rolling boil.
Cool.
Then add mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Add miniature marshmallows and pineapple chunks.

title: white chocolate blueberry pie
directions: To prepare crust, combine crumbs and butter. Press into a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool completely on a rack.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine cooked macaroni, broccoli, celery, carrots, onion and green pepper in a large bowl.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble
biscuits
in
pan.
Pour sugar, cocoa and milk over this
to
moisten
crumbs well.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes. Add eggs,
melted butter, vanilla and flour and mix well.
Add more milk,
if needed.
Pour into well-greased pan and bake at 450° until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt to oil mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until it tests done.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook bow tie according to package.
Melt 1 stick oleo and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add noodles and stir.
Peel and cook potatoes.
Whip together with 3/4 pound Velveeta cheese, 1/2 stick oleo and a little milk.
Saute onion in 1/2 stick oleo.
Layer noodles, potatoes and onion.
Top with 1/4 pound Velveeta.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroon pudding
directions: Heat milk and sugar.
Stir.
Break in macaroons.
Add cornstarch, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add almond flavoring.
Serve cold with whipped cream or any plain sauce.

title: parmesan chicken nuggets
directions: Spray baking rack and place on a baking sheet. Combine corn flake crumbs and cheese. Cut chicken into finger size pieces. Dip into milk, then roll in crumbs, coating completely.
Place on rack.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes until golden and cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Beat in eggs one at a time.
Mix in nuts and chips and vanilla. Bake at 350° in rectangle greased pan.
Cut in squares after about 10 minutes out of oven.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook the frozen spinach and drain well.
Then combine all the ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: party wieners
directions: Mix together and place on low heat, stirring until smooth. Cut wieners in bite size pieces and heat thoroughly in mixture (do not boil).
Serve hot from chafing dish.
Yields sauce for 1 pound of wieners (you may save sauce in refrigerator, reheat and use again).
Try this for something different and to please the men.

title: tabooli
directions: In a large bowl, layer ingredients as follows:
wheat on bottom (dry), tomatoes, cumin and salt, lemon juice, cucumbers, onions and chopped parsley.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate at least 3 hours, preferably overnight.
Before serving, add olive oil and mix thoroughly.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt one stick of oleo and mix with crumbs.
Spread evenly into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat together for no less than 15 minutes the eggs, sugar and remaining 2 sticks of oleo.
Spoon mixture over the crumb layer and arrange sliced bananas over the top.
The next layer is drained crushed pineapple, then the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and decorate with cherries. Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Add onion.
Then coat with following dressing.

title: frozen sandwiches
directions: Mix together.
Put on buns.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
From freezer to oven.
Turn oven to 350° and heat approximately 20 minutes.

title: oriental chicken soup
directions: Brown chicken chunks in oil.
Add soy sauce.
Add mixed vegetables and water chestnuts with all juice.
Add water.
Bring to a boil; add broccoli and egg noodles.
Add more soy sauce if you like and cook until noodles are done.
If you need more water, go ahead.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; divide in half. Shape each portion into a ball and roll in pecans. Cover and chill. Serve with shortbread cookies and gingersnaps or apple and pear slices. Yield: 2 (4-inch) cheese balls.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Soak bread crumbs in part of liquid.
Fry onions and celery in oil or fat until brown.
Beat eggs and combine rest of ingredients.
Add remainder of milk.
Potato water is real good to mix with the milk also.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chilli dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in 9 x 13 pan. Spread canned chili as next layer. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve hot with chips on the side. Spoon dip onto chips or scoop!

title: finger roll sandwiches
directions: Mix together.
Spread between 3 dozen buns (4 dozen party buns).
Wrap in foil and toast in 400° oven about 20 minutes.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: oreo cupcake cones
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes, at high speed; place ice cream cones in muffin tins or onto jelly roll pan.
Fill cones 1/2 full with batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until cake springs up when touched in center.
Decorate as desired with assorted candies.

title: peach yam bake
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and nutmeg in bowl.
Stir in margarine until crumbly.
Mix in pecans; arrange yams and peaches in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over yams.
Bake until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Have butter, sour cream and eggs at room temperature. Sift together, flour and soda. Cream butter and sugar well. Add eggs one at a time. Mix well on low to medium speed. Add vanilla and almond. Beginning with flour, alternately add flour and cream cheese to mixture. Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 325° for one hour or slightly longer. May spray pan with Bakers Secret instead of greasing.

title: christmas twist
directions: Crumble first 4 ingredients with pie fork.
Stir yeast into flour and sour cream (you can whip cream). Add 1 egg and vanilla. Knead the bread dough. Cover with a damp cloth and chill for 2+ hours.

title: brian's pan lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings; stir.
Add noodles; bring to boil in deep skillet or large saucepan.
Turn down heat to fast simmer; let cook until sauce thickens and most of the water is absorbed into the noodles. Stir in Mozzarella.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: In a large skillet, combine onion, garlic and ground beef. Cook until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Stir in ingredients, except spaghetti.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain. Serve meat sauce over hot spaghetti.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 4 servings.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, water and vanilla together until very smooth.
Pour mixture over butter. Drain peaches and spoon over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° until brown on top.
Serve with vanilla ice cream and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil and let cool.
Blend cream of coconut with lemonade in blender to mix together.
Mix all and freeze.
Stir a few times while freezing.
Add 7-Up to serve.

title: crock-pot beef tips
directions: Roll beef tips or stew meat in flour and brown in a small amount of oil.
Cool, put into crock-pot sprayed with Pam, add 1 package brown gravy for each 1 pound of beef.
Increase water by 2 cups for each package of gravy.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Salt to taste.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Roll chops
in flour to which salt and pepper have been added. Brown
chops and place in greased casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients, stir well and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
When well blended, add Rice Krispies.
Spoon onto cookie sheet covered by wax paper.
Refrigerate to set.
Store in covered container.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for at least 24 hours.
Cook or grill as desired.

title: artichoke bake
directions: Sprinkle garlic powder, salt and cloves on layered sliced onions, green pepper, zucchini, eggplant and quartered tomatoes. Salt and pepper top layer.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Take off lid and cook off all juice.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Fold in sour
cream and vanilla.
Add baking powder, salt and flour.
Fold in berries. Now combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/3 of cake batter into greased and floured tube pan, then sprinkle brown sugar mixture.
Add last of cake batter.
Now take a knife and lightly swirl or cut through cake mixture.
Bake
at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: red raspberry dessert
directions: Pour water over jello and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Place frozen raspberries in hot mixture to chill fast.
Pour over next layer and chill until firm.
Ice with large container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Chill overnight.

title: sheep herder's fondue(party appetizer)
directions: Mix all the above except the bread and let marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Leave bread out, uncovered, one day to harden. Slice top off as a lid. Take out the insides of the loaf in bite size pieces. Toast and use as dippers.
Put mixture in bread bowl just before serving and arrange dippers or crackers around sides.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Blend together oil, margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add salt and flavorings.
Put in a cold oven to bake at 325° for 45 minutes, then increase temperature to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried cornbread
directions: In medium bowl, mix cornmeal, sugar and salt. Slowly stir in boiling water. Cover and let set for 10 minutes. Add egg, milk, butter and flour. Cook on hot griddle like pancakes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Or a 9-inch ready made graham cracker crust.

title: sue's guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips. Optional:
crumbled bacon and/or tomato bits.

title: juicy apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with butter.
Place apple slices in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Toss to coat, then pour into baking dish.
In a medium bowl, mix butter, remaining 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon flour, brown sugar, remaining 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg until crumbly.
Stir in oats.
Sprinkle over apples, making sure edges are coated.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until apples are tender.
Serve with evaporated milk.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter shake
directions: Slice the banana.
Mix with the milk and peanut butter in a blender.
Makes 6 small servings.

title: coconut eggnog pie
directions: Combine 2 2/3 cups coconut with butter.
Press evenly into 9-inch crust.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown. Cool.

title: bran rolls
directions: Combine together Crisco, boiling water, sugar, Bran Buds and salt.
Add to Crisco mixture the lukewarm water and yeast.
Add to mixture the eggs and 1/2 flour; beat until light.
Add remaining flour, more if needed.
Let rise until doubled.
Knead.
Place in 2 well-greased loaf pans and let rise.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare long sheet cake as directed.
Leave in pan.
Boil sugar and milk.
Prick holes in cake.
Gradually pour sugar and milk solution all over cake.
Refrigerate 3 or more days.
When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each cheese in half.
Place one half on top of each cutlet.
Starting with a short end, tightly roll up cutlets, jelly roll style.
Tie securely with string.
On waxed paper, combine flour and pepper.
Mix well.
Add cutlets, tossed gently to coat.

title: savory baked spaghetti(serves 6)
directions: Slowly cook onions and garlic in oil 5 minutes.
Add hamburg; cook, stirring occasionally, until meat loses red color.
Stir in salt, pepper and tomatoes (put tomatoes through sieve or squash with hands.)
Simmer covered 30 minutes.
Add chili powder and water.
Start oven to 325°.
Break half of uncooked spaghetti in greased casserole.
Pour half of sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with half of cheese.
Break in rest of spaghetti; add rest of sauce and sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Bake covered 35 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer or until brown.

title: vegetable nachos
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cut 3 (2 1/4-inch) circles from each tortilla using a biscuit cutter.
Dip tortillas in water; drain on paper towels.
Place rounds in a single layer on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until chips are crisp and begin to brown.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Spoon 2 teaspoons vegetable mixture on each tortilla chip; divide cheese evenly among chips.
Broil 6 inches from heat 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Yields 26 appetizers.

title: borscht(serves about 4)
directions: *Found in the kosher food section of many supermarkets; lemon juice may also be used.

title: sunday beef stew
directions: Roll beef cubes in the flour and brown in kettle. Cover with the water and add the seasonings.
Bring to a boil and simmer over low heat until tender.
Add the carrots, potatoes, onions and more water, if needed, and cook over medium heat until vegetables are done (about 1 hour).

title: striped delight(dessert)
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth. Fold in half the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight. Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding.
Garnish with mini chocolate chips.

title: peanut butter-ice cream pie
directions: Combine
peanut
butter,
topping
and ice cream;
stir until blended.
Spoon into crust and freeze at least 8 hours. Serve garnished with additional topping.

title: filbert kisses
directions: Mix yolks with sugar; add nuts, unbleached and ground fine. Beat egg whites and fold into other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased pans and bake in slow oven (250°) for 1/2 hour or until crisp.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces; brown in oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes; add carrots and green pepper.
Combine all other ingredients, including the can of pineapple and juice. Cover and simmer 10 or more minutes.
Serve over Minute rice.

title: elephant ears
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Heat margarine until melted, (set aside). Stir flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
Stir in milk and 3 tablespoons of the melted margarine until dough forms.
Sprinkle a surface lightly with flour, turn dough onto surface.
Knead 10 times.
Roll dough with a rolling pin or pat with hands into a rectangle 9 x 5-inches.
Brush with remaining melted margarine, using a pastry brush.
Sprinkle with mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Roll dough up tightly, beginning at narrow end.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal. Cut into 4 equal pieces with sharp knife.
Place cut sides up on cookie sheet.
Pat each into a 6-inch circle.
Sprinkle with more sugar and bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet with spatula.
Let cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 Elephant Ears.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs together.
Add rest of ingredients, adding apples last.
Add cinnamon and nuts, if desired.

title: ada's carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together next 4 ingredients and add.
Fold in carrots, pineapple and nutmeats. Pour into buttered bread pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: butterscotch pies
directions: Scald milk in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Combine dry ingredients and add milk gradually, stirring until smooth. Return to saucepan and cook, stirring until hot and mixture is beginning to thicken.
Add small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks and stir.
Add egg yolks to remaining mixture in saucepan. Cook for 2 minutes over low heat or until mixture is very thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shells and add meringue and bake.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix all together and spread on bread.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Grease baking dish.
Layer chicken, Swiss cheese, soup and Stove Top stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed baby red potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scrub potatoes; arrange on a baking sheet and bake 45 minutes until tender; remove from oven.
While potatoes cook, in a small bowl, combine the ham, mushrooms, bacon, cream cheese and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Let potatoes cool 15 minutes or until you can handle them.
Slice 1/4 off the top of potato; scoop out a few teaspoons of flesh.
Fill cavity of each potato with the cream cheese mixture; sprinkle tops of potatoes with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Put back in oven to warm, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with dollops of sour cream. Makes 10 to 15 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Grease or spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Line pan with rolls to make crust.
Peel and slice tomatoes.
Place on crust.
Add salt and pepper.
Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in oil until tender.
Pour over tomatoes.
Mix mayo and cheese and put on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: grilled rosemary chicken
directions: Pound breasts between sheets of plastic until flat.
Combine remaining ingredients in an unbreakable container with a tight lid that is large enough to hold all the chicken.
Toss or spread marinade over chicken, coating both sides.
Refrigerate, tossing occasionally.
Cook over hot coals or grill for about 2 minutes. Turn and cook another 2 minutes, until done.

title: chili casserole
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour chili on top. Then sprinkle cheese on top of that. Top with crushed Fritos.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: congo cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening; add sugar.
Stir and let cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients.
Add water, then nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into a 16 1/2 x 10-inch greased pan; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cut into finger length bars an inch wide, when slightly cooled.
Very good!

title: pumpkin pickles
directions: *Do not use a Jack 'O Lantern pumpkin.
Use fresh spices and firm pumpkin.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Refrigerate. Will keep several days.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes; dissolve over boiling water.
Add lemon juice, sugar and all fruits.
Stir gently.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Spoon into your favorite mold.
Cover with plastic wrap. Freeze.

title: pfister salad
directions: Clean and dry lettuce, cauliflower and onion.
Tear lettuce into pieces.
Slice cauliflower and onion thin. Fry bacon and crumble or slice thin and then fry.
Mix lettuce, cauliflower, bacon and onion and set aside.

title: california beef rice skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add onion; stir.
Stir in beef broth, water and rice.
(Optional:
I like to season with garlic salt and Creole seasoning at this point.)
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Add bell pepper and tomato.
Cook for another 5 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: hot dog stew
directions: This is sort of a poor man's goulash, something quick and dirty that doesn't take much time but is pretty good and a lot of fun as well.

title: red pepper biscuits
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together biscuit mix, Parmesan cheese, oregano and cayenne. Add roasted peppers and milk to biscuit mixture. Stir just until moistened. Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes in a 425° oven or until browned. Yields 1 dozen.

title: "kourambiethes" - powdered sugar butter cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat the butter about 10 minutes.
Add egg yolk and powdered sugar; beat 10 minutes longer.
Add enough flour to make a semi-sweet dough.
Roll in balls and place on cookie sheet that is lined with wax paper, about 2-inches apart. Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from cookie sheets. Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheets, which are dusted with powdered sugar.
When cool, sift powdered sugar over the balls. Will keep in Tupperware or in freezer.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook onions and ground beef until meat is browned and onions are tender.
Drain fat.
Add seasonings and tomatoes, simmer for approximately 1 hour.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 315° in pan coated with cooking spray for 1 hour.

title: holiday punch
directions: Blend 3 pints of softened ice cream and milk in a punch bowl. Add peppermint extract and a few drops of coloring.
Gradually add ginger ale and stir gently.
Cut in remaining ice cream to float in small pieces.
Serves 32.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine the onion, soup, sour cream and carrots and fold in squash.
Spread stuffing mix on greased 8 x 10-inch glass dish. Spoon in vegetable mix.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cucumber cole slaw
directions: In a food processor, use the grater attachment.
Grate the cabbage, carrots and cucumber.
Put the vegetables into a medium size bowl, mixing in the celery seed and dressing.
Chill before serving.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Place all vegetables and bouillon cubes in large kettle. Cover with water and cook until potatoes are tender.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.
In separate kettle, melt butter.
Add milk and cheese.
Stir with wire whisk until cheese melts.
Add to vegetables and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add carrots and nuts.
Grease 2 loaf pans, flour also.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese. Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, stirring just until blended. Stir in coconut and flavorings. Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely. Yield: one 10-inch cake.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Break 20 crackers into fourths; layer in bottom of casserole. Arrange half of the oysters on top.
Dot with butter or margarine; sprinkle with pepper.
Repeat the layer.
Arrange remaining crackers.
Dot with butter.
Mix cream and oyster liquid together; pour over all.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown, but not dry.

title: diabetic baked beans
directions: Rinse, sort and soak beans in water to cover overnight.
Drain beans.
Combine with onions, apples, juice, diet maple syrup and Sweet 'N Low in baking dish.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat. Bake, covered, at 300° for 4 to 6 hours or until apples and onions have cooked down.
Stir in
hot sauce and barley miso.
Adjust seasoning (pepper and salt).

title: tawny pumpkin pie
directions: Blend together eggs and pumpkin. Stir in sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves. Blend in evaporated milk. Pour into pie shell. Bake in hot 400° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pie comes out clean. Cool completely on rack.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef with diced onion, then drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Place a piece of fry bread on a plate.
Layer with chili, cooked pinto beans, lettuce, onion, tomato, grated cheese, picante sauce (your choice, mild, hot, medium).

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in square pan.
Remove from heat when it starts to boil.
Add peanut butter and cornflakes.
Spoon onto wax paper in bite size pieces.
Yields 24 to 36 pieces.

title: chili
directions: Add chili powder and allspice to cans of whole tomatoes, tomato paste and sauce.
Add water and simmer 1 hour.
Add kidney beans.

title: georgia's special cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° in 2 or 3 layers.
Poke holes in cake for topping to soak in some.

title: rum cake
directions: Beat all together and put in greased bundt pan.
If you want you can put 1/2 c. nuts in bottom of pan and put 1/2 c. on top of cake.
Bake at 345° for 45 min.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers and other appetizers.

title: lorene's fruit pizza
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.	Smooth on 2 greased and floured pizza pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
After cool, spread
with Cool Whip. Top with fresh fruit (example: strawberries, peaches, bananas and kiwi fruit).

title: rainbow jello
directions: Spray Bundt cake pan or tube pan with light coat of Pam. Empty one box of Jell-O in glass bowl.
Add 1 1/4 cups of boiling water; mix.
Then separate the Jell-O in 2 equal bowls.
Pour one bowl in cake pan.
Place in icebox for 1 hour.

title: syrian potato salad
directions: Peel and dice the cooked potatoes.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to the potatoes.
Mix and chill well before serving.

title: tarragon flour
directions: Mix the ingredients thoroughly; store in refrigerator.
Use for chicken cutlets, pork chops, etc., when sauteing.
Excellent flavor for coating before sauteing.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except ham.
Cook on low heat until mixture has thickened slightly.
Stir in 16 ounces of cooked ham (sliced paper thin or shredded). Heat through.

title: spicy orange chicken
directions: In wok or large skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken 1/3 at a time.
Stir-fry 3 minutes or until browned. Return all chicken to wok.
Add orange peel, garlic and ginger. Stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Stir into chicken.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cook frozen spinach as directed on box; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients with cooked spinach; mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until firm.

title: orange blossom special
directions: In medium bowl, combine orange and lemon juice with powdered sugar.
Allow to sit at least 8 hours in refrigerator.
Stir occasionally.
This mixture will have the consistency of tomato soup.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan, lined with graham crackers (whole and laid flat on bottom of pan).
Beat puddings with milk for 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers. Place another layer of crackers and then more pudding.
Then cover with graham crackers.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: microwave meatloaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Put into microwavable loaf pan or casserole dish.
Mix tomato sauce and brown sugar to make topping. Set aside.
Cook meatloaf in microwave on high for 20 minutes. Pour off liquid and add topping.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer or until done.

title: praline-topped sweet potato
directions: Mash potatoes and remove all lumps.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Make topping. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: microwaved "baked" apples
directions: Wash, then partially peel and core apples.
Cut each into 6 to 8 wedges.
Stir in pudding and brown sugar.
Pour into baking dish with lid.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Drizzle with water and dot with butter.
Cook on High for about 20 minutes.
Stir; if any apples are still firm, cook a few more minutes until done. Delicious with vanilla ice cream!

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies(kids of all ages like these cookies)
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch glass pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes until top slightly browns.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: potato deluxe casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges in cup. Fill with water to make 1 cup. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Add sherbet and lemon juice. Stir until blended.
Leave in pan and set in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Add oranges and put in mold. Chill.

title: a happy child recipe
directions: Take twelve months.
Clean them thoroughly of all bitterness, hate and jealousy.
Then arrange each month into 28, 30 or 31 parts, but don't make up the whole batch at once.
Prepare it one day at a time out of these ingredients.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cook frozen vegetables as package directs; drain.

title: teiglach (dough cookies)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and eggs to a stiff dough.
Knead it firmly.

title: one dish bake from leftovers
directions: Mix broccoli, meat and onion in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix soups and 1 cup milk together. Pour over meat and broccoli mixture; stir. Mix Bisquick and milk; pour evenly over meat and vegetables. Sprinkle with parsley flakes if desired. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until light and golden brown. Let stand at least 5 minutes before serving.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Place meat cubes and minced onion into a pot.
Measure 1 cup water in a 2-cup measure.
Add all other ingredients (except 1/2 cup water and flour).
Stir together thoroughly and pour over meat.
Bring to a boil, then simmer several hours until tender.

title: chile
directions: Put ground beef and onions in pan with a little water and let cook until onions are done.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles, using package directions; drain.
Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Mix ground beef with spaghetti sauce.
Spread 3 spoonfuls in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer noodles, remaining meat sauce, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese, 1/3 at a time, in prepared dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Wrap hamburger buns in aluminum foil; heat in oven 15 minutes.
In medium skillet, cook and stir meat until brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into warm buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: steak and kidney pie
directions: Put beef, kidneys, mushrooms, onion, parsley, bay leaf and salt in 4-quart casserole.
Add 2 cups water. Cut butter into flour until it resembles coarse meal.
Add milk and mix lightly to form soft dough.
Turn
out onto floured board and roll 1/8-inch thick.
Place on top of casserole.
Cut slits in dough.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: orange spinach salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in salad bowl.
Pour dressing over salad and toss.
(Good for people to eat with mitral valve prolapse.)

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, egg and almond extract.
Gradually blend in flour.
Fill cookie press and drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt.
Wash and skin chicken.
Dip chicken in salad dressing, then in bread crumb mixture.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, turning chicken once.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash bananas and mix soda with them.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix cinnamon with flour.
Add bananas to creamed mixture, then add flour; mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: onion soup(3 servings)
directions: Melt butter in oil.
Add onions slowly.
Cook until soft, about 10 minutes.
Be careful not to brown onions.
Sprinkle flour over mixture.
Stir and add liquid, slowly so it does not lump. Add salt, pepper and Accent.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Slice French type bread 1/2-inch thick.
Crisp toast in 350° oven.
Pour soup with lots of the onion in each serving, into 3 bowls; cover with slice of bread, cover bread with Mozzarella or Swiss cheese, shredded.
Cover that with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° to bubbly hot, then put under broiler to brown.

title: egg bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups of the flour and the yeast.
In a saucepan, heat milk, sugar, butter and salt just until warm (115° to 120°) and butter is almost melted; stir constantly.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in as much remaining flour as you can mix in with a spoon.

title: manhattan fish chowder
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onion until tender.
Add potato, celery, tomatoes and seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add corn and fish.
Heat to boiling.
Slice roll; toast.
Place a slice of bread to each soup bowl.
Ladle chowder over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: aunt eddie's apple pie
directions: Place apples in unbaked pie crust.
Mix sugar, flour and spices.
Add the cream and mix well.
Pour mixture over sliced apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° until done (about 45 minutes).

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oatmeal and water; set aside to cool.
Cream shortening, brown sugar and regular sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and soda; fold into creamed mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350° or until tests done.

title: apricot delight
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water and cold water until Jell-O is dissolved. Add pineapple, pecans, bananas and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until firm.
Mix Dream Whip topping mix according to package directions. Set aside.
Mix sugar, egg, juice and butter.
Cook until thick over medium heat.
Cool.
Stir in cream cheese.
Add custard mixture to Dream Whip mixture.
Spread over Jell-O and chill.

title: waffles
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour 1/2 cup batter onto waffle iron.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all canned food.
Stir well and let stand for several hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop by tablespoons and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix ingredients, including 1 cup flour; beat until smooth; add remainder of flour.
Put in bowl, cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
In morning, divide dough in 4 parts, form each part into ball, roll out; cut into 8 pie shaped wedges.
Roll up crescent style.
Raise 3 hours.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes and mash.
Combine potatoes, butter and egg.
Mix sugar with flour and salt.
Add to mixture along with vanilla.
Dissolve soda in milk and add to potato mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: always good pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt until crumbly.
Beat together water, vinegar and egg.
Add to first mixture.
Prepare and place in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
This pie crust is better for pies like pecan, etc., that you cook in the crust.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: In a covered saucepan, simmer celery, onion, bouillon and water until vegetables are tender.
Add milk, salt and pepper and simmer, uncovered, until hot.
Makes 1 quart.

title: early bird granola
directions: Place oats in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add sugar, wheat germ, coconut, nuts and mix.
Add oil, honey and vanilla.
Mix and bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring often to brown evenly.
Cool and store in refrigerator. Makes 8 cups.

title: southern cannonballs
directions: Mix well; form into walnut sized balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: mamma mia meat sauce
directions: In a large (6-quart) pot, cook the meat until it loses its pinkness.
Drain the fat, then return to the heat; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce the heat.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Makes about 5 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir cooked chicken, 1/2 sauce and cream cheese until smooth. Spoon 1/3 cup mixture onto each tortilla and roll up.
Place, seam side down, into lightly greased baking dish.
Stir cheese spread and milk into pan and smooth.
Pour sauce over tortillas and cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sunday morning gravy
directions: Brown sausage; add flour, milk and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until mixture thickens. Serve over biscuits or toast.

title: waldorf rice salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring juice to a boil.
Stir in rice, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Chill.
Stir in celery, apple, walnuts and yogurt. Serves 4.

title: mulled tomato juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven or large kettle.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve in small mugs.
Yields 15 servings (about 3/4 cup each).

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix corn and eggs together. Add to dry ingredients.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples with rinds and seeds.
Run through sieve.
Combine ingredients except cinnamon oil.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add cinnamon oil and seal.
Yield:
6 1/2 pints.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops to taste.
Brown chops quickly in 2 tablespoons oil.
Place chops in 9 x 12-inch cooking dish.
Add dry rice to skillet where chops were browned.
Stir rice constantly until brown.
Place rice in baking dish over chops. Pour can of tomatoes over rice and chops.
Cover well with foil. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: In a pan, place chicken pieces; remove skin, if desired.
Mix catsup with Coca-Cola and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: spinach dip
directions: Salt to taste.
Boil frozen spinach according to directions. Drain well.
In bowl, mix spinach with other ingredients.
Stir until smooth. Refrigerate.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hot dogs, flour and oil or shortening.
Roll hot dogs in flour, then in batter.
Heat oil or shortening to 375°.
Fry dogs for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix the ingredients. Form into 23 balls.
Freeze until needed. Makes 23 crusts.

title: wiener stew
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots, onions and celery in saltwater until soft.
Add milk, sliced wieners and pepper and bring to a boil. Thicken with flour and butter that have been rubbed together to form a smooth paste.
Serves 8.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, karo and water to a boil.
Add peanuts and bring to the hard crack stage.
Very quickly add butter, salt & soda. As soon as the last ingredients are mixed in well, pour on to a well greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into small pieces.

title: hot and spicy sloppy joes(serves 8)
directions: In a large skillet cook ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sift your 3 cups of flour and set aside. Put your yeast in your 1/2 cup of warm water and let it melt, then mix with rest of your ingredients. Put egg; beat, then Crisco, salt, sugar and your 1/2 cup of water and yeast that you have mixed up also add your other 1/2 cup of water. Mix together and add a little flour at a time until you get almost all of the 3 cups of flour in. Put in bowl and cover with Saran Wrap. Let stand 2 hours or until it doubles in size or put in refrigerator overnight. Take out of bowl and knead, knead and knead. Roll out and cut into biscuits. Put in pan and let rise 1 1/2 or 2 hours where it is warm, then put in 400° oven and cook until done, about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use 1 1/2 cups of broth and one pack of stuffing mix and place on bottom of baking dish.
Spread chicken over stuffing. Pour 2 cans of cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Use the other 1 1/2 cups of broth and one pack of stuffing mix and place on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Using lowest speed of electric mixer, blend oil, molasses and egg.
Add sugar and blend.
Gradually add dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball in granulated sugar.
Place on Teflon baking sheet and sprinkle each cookie with 2 to 3 drops of water.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg into boiling water.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add lemon juice and coloring.
Pack apples into clean, quart jars to within 1 inch of top.
Pour hot syrup over apples.
Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: skillet meal(main dish)
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery in oil. Add tomatoes and coarsely shredded cabbage to this mixture. Salt and pepper. Cover and cook 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry daiquiri slush
directions: Mix Jell-O and Kool-Aid with hot water to dissolve.
Put all ingredients together and freeze, mixing every hour or so to slush.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: almononnaise
directions: Cover almonds with boiling water, then cool.
Slip off the skins; grind almonds to a fine powder in blender.
Add half of the soy milk, yeast, garlic powder and seasoning; blend well, then add the remaining soy water to make a smooth cream.
With blender on low, remove insert on top and drizzle in the oil in a thin stream. Keep blender on low.
Add lemon juice and vinegar.
Blend on low for 1 minute.
Will keep 10 days to 2 weeks, tightly sealed in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; mix with cheese, sugar and flour.
Put in a baking dish.
Crunch Ritz crackers and put over top.
Melt margarine and pour over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: floating fruit parfaits
directions: Divide fruit into 6 parfait glasses.
Stir boiling water into gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in water and 3/4 cup ice cubes. Pour 3/4 cup gelatin over fruit in glasses.
Refrigerate 20 minutes, until set, not firm.
Stir 1 cup Cool Whip into remaining gelatin and whisk until smooth.
Spoon over gelatin.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip.

title: 4 b's tomato soup #2
directions: Simmer all but the cream for 1 hour.
Add the cream and heat through, but do not boil.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Layer broccoli and grated onions; pour melted butter and undiluted cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups over broccoli.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: strawberry chiffon pies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix strawberry Jell-O to this and set aside to cool.
Whip the Carnation milk, which has been chilled.
Mix this to the strawberry mixture.
Pour into crust made from vanilla wafers.
This makes two pies.

title: spicy cranberry orange mold
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar and set aside.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Spoon into 6 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold. Serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir until combined. Fold in whipped topping and pecans.
Spoon into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish and chill until firm.
Cut salad into squares to serve. Serves 8.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients together.
Whip on high until like cream.
Then add rest (rotate) until well mixed.
Grease tube pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Some ovens take 15 minutes more.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put rye bread on cookie sheet; spread each piece with mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap and freeze.
After frozen, put in Ziploc bags in small numbers.
Take them from freeze and put under broiler in oven or can be warmed up in microwave.
Make this one ahead.
Great for unexpected guests!

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix with fingers.
Roll in balls and dip in 1 pound melted chocolate.

title: seasoned oven potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1 to 1 1/2-inch cubes.
In a 12 x 8-inch dish combine parsley, onion, salt and oil.
Blend.
Add potatoes. Toss and coat them well.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Drain off excess fat.

title: choc-chip banana bread
directions: Combine 1 Tbsp. flour with the chocolate chips, set aside. Mix remaining ingredients. Fold floured chocolate chips into mixture. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in an unbaked pie shell for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Line cupcake papers with 1 vanilla wafer, flat side down.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla flavor in mixer.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Top with favorite topping (cherry, strawberry or blueberry pie filling).

title: southwest lemon fruit tart
directions: Prepare Pecan Crust, cool.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or brown.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Melt margarine and mix. Add vinegar and vanilla, then pecans. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: aunt lucy's goulash
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in an electric skillet in 2 tablespoons butter.
Then pour in 1 large can of tomato juice. Let come to a boil.
Add box of macaroni; let come to a boil. Pinch up ground beef and drop in boiling tomato juice.
Cover and cook until all liquid is absorbed.
Top with Velveeta cheese. Kids really love this!

title: jalapeno squares
directions: Butter 8 1/2 x 13-inch dish.
Grate and press Cheddar cheese into dish.
Take peppers, chop and sprinkle over grated cheese. Grate Monterey Jack or Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle over peppers. Beat eggs and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let rise until cup is full.
Scald milk; cream together butter and sugar, then beaten eggs and salt.
Add milk with flour and beat after each addition.
Add yeast and beat well again.
Turn out on floured board and knead until satiny.
Place in greased bowl; cover and set in warm place to rise until double in bulk (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Knead again and cut into rolls.
Let rise again until ready to bake.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Rinse frozen broccoli under running cold water to separate.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Spread in dish. Bake, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, 60 to 65 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered until cheese is melted, about 1 minute longer.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: oil-vinegar cole slaw
directions: Boil
and cool oil, vinegar, sugar and salt and pepper. Shred cabbage,
carrots
and
onions.
Pour cool mixture over vegetables.
Mix well; refrigerate.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries and mix.
Put half of mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Cover with sour cream and spoon remaining Jell-O mixture over layer of cream.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix together and spread on buns.
Bake at 275° for about 25 minutes.
Sandwiches can be individually wrapped in foil and frozen.
In this case, let them thaw before baking.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water with salt.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin-date muffins
directions: In a large bowl put flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and nutmeg.
In another bowl put pumpkin, oil, brown sugar, milk, beaten eggs and vanilla, mix these ingredients until blended.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin mixture and stir to combine.
Stir in dates.
Spoon batter into muffin pan (grease pan or use paper cups).
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.
Freezes well.

title: pea salad
directions: Cut up chestnuts in small pieces and marinate overnight in the oil, vinegar and sugar. Drain mixture.
Mix all ingredients well. Line bowl with lettuce leaves and arrange salad.
Serves 6.

title: amazing cleaner
directions: Let a quart of buttermilk set until thick.
Pour 1 quart boiling water over it, stirring at the same time.
Let set a few minutes. Cheese will go to the bottom.
Pour off the water.
Put cheese in cloth to drain 1/2 day.
Add salt according to taste.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of nuts. Roll into 2 cheese balls. Roll cheese balls into remaining cup of nuts.

title: mexican snack squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Place crosswise on 15 x 10-inch ungreased baking pan.
Press on bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust.
Seal the seams.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Spread beans over crust within 1/2-inch of edges.
Mix taco seasoning and sour cream together and spread over beans.
Layer other ingredients over sour cream.
Cover; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Serve with salsa.

title: crab spread
directions: Chop meat until fine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill. This is great with crackers.

title: sweet cinnamon pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in bowl; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add milk, sugar, 1/3 cup butter, egg, salt and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Beat in enough remaining flour to make an easily-handled dough.

title: berry sweet pancakes
directions: Mix Jiffy mix, milk and brown sugar together.
Add vanilla and strawberry jam.
Pour batter onto heated griddle.

title: creamy chicken chowder
directions: Cover chicken with water; add garlic and celery and boil until done.
Dice chicken when cooked; set aside with broth.
Scrub clean potatoes; dice with peel on and cook in chicken broth.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Roll crust to fit oblong pan.
Pour mixture over crust.
Top with other crust.
Roll and flute edges.
Cut slits in center.
Cook, uncovered, in 425° oven until crust is brown, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken cheese enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut up broiler-fryer.
Bring water to boil in 4-quart pan.
Add chicken pieces and onion.
Reduce heat to medium and boil 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from water; allow to cool.
Skin and bone chicken.
Cut chicken into small pieces. Stir cream of chicken soup, green chiles and chicken into boiling water.
Remove from heat.
Drain off most of the liquid from the chicken mixture, reserving it in a 3-quart bowl for later.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, lay tortillas one at a time, filling each with 1/4 cup of chicken mixture, then rolling them up and laying them uniformly in the dish.
Stir any remaining chicken mixture, sour cream and cheese into the reserved liquid.
Stir until well mixed, then spread evenly over rolled tortillas.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub the inside of a large wooden bowl with the garlic cloves. Remove the garlic cloves and finely chop. Add the egg yolks, remaining garlic, anchovies and mustard to the bowl. Whisk until all of the ingredients are incorporated. Whisk in the lemon juice. Slowly drizzle in the olive oil while whisking constantly. Whisk until all of the ingredients are incorporated.

Season the dressing with salt and pepper. Gently tear the lettuce into bite-size portions and add to the salad bowl. Using a handheld grater, grate the cheese into the bowl. Add the croutons. Toss the salad
completely and re-season if necessary. Serve the salad on cold salad plates. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion and celery and saute.
Add potatoes and broth.
Cover and let cook until potatoes are tender.
In batches puree mixture in blender.
Return to pan and add milk and seasonings, either add cheese to melt or serve as side dish.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cake mix as says on box.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer each ingredient.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over top of this and brown.

title: spring salad
directions: Wash greens; toss with vegetables.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cover vegetables with water and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain and mix milk with one can cream of chicken soup.
Fold into drained squash.
Butter baking dish; put in half of stuffing mix. Add Squash and cover with rest of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar gradually.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Add to the eggs and sugar.
Scald the milk and butter together and add vanilla.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (layers about 20 minutes).

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Set to jiggle stage.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Feeds 12.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Italian dressing together.
Pour over cooked pastas and other ingredients.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip together potatoes, eggs, sugar, vanilla and flour.
Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: gramma's candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and slice lengthwise.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt margarine.
Add brown sugar, lemon extract, cinnamon and water.
Bring to a gentle boil and add sliced sweet potatoes.
Heat for several minutes on each side (sweet potatoes should be hot when removed from skillet).
Remove potatoes to a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onions.
Season with salt and pepper; put meat in casserole dish.
Drain corn; place over meat.
Spread mushroom soup over corn.
Add a layer of sliced cheese.
Place tater tots on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
If desired, place cheese on top of tater tots just long enough to melt.

title: blueberry fried pies
directions: Cook until thick. Place 1 tablespoon of filling in center of crust; fold in half and seal edges with fork. Fry in hot oil. Cool. Enjoy.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-O in large bowl.
Tear Circus peanuts into small bites and stir until they dissolve, then add pineapple, juice and all.
Let set until it starts to jell, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and soda together; stir in with margarine.
Mix flour alternately with buttermilk; add about 3/4 cup nuts.
Grease pans with Crisco and dust with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 2 loaf pans.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown chicken and onions.
When brown and tender, remove only chicken from skillet.
Put in mustard, parsley, soup and milk.
Heat for 5 minutes, then return chicken and heat through.

title: pastitsio
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is browned; drain off excess fat.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, thyme and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: spicy dipping sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients 1 minute before serving catfish. Check seasonings carefully.

title: angel pudding
directions: Mix milk, gelatine and sugar. Soak 1/2 hour.
Add yolks, sugar and salt to gelatine mixture and cook until thickened. Stir constantly.
Let cool. Add whipped cream and fold in egg whites and vanilla. Crush the graham crackers.
Put half of the crumbs in bottom of dish, then pudding mixture, then rest of crumbs on top. Chill before serving.

title: chocolate syrup for ice cream
directions: Stir ingredients together gradually to make a paste.
Boil for 3 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil or bake chicken breasts.
Cool and then shred the chicken.
Mix soups, sour cream, onion and cheese, then stir in the chicken.
Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and place unsalted nacho chips on the bottom, a layer of the chicken mixture, chips, etc. and put cheese on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: In small saucepan, heat corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 cup of syrup in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange potatoes in syrup; top with remaining syrup.
Bake, basting often, for 20 minutes, until well glazed.
Serves 12.

title: luann's hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain grease. Add butter, flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes. Add cream of mushroom soup and simmer for 5 minutes. Cool to serving temperature and add sour cream.

title: cheese ball(serves 25)
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley and nuts.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill overnight.

title: sweet glazed roast
directions: Finely chop scallops.
Combine all ingredients (except cranberry and picante).
Mix well and pour into loaf pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Heat cranberry jelly sauce and picante and pour over roast.
Serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; pat into pie pan or quiche pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until lightly brown.
Serve from oven with tortilla chips.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix; finish filling gallon jar with water.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Arrange the cake around the inside of a glass serving dish. Over this, pour the wine or sherry.
When the cake has soaked up most of the wine, spread with a layer of strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix butter, Crisco, milk and salt.
Add egg and flour mixture and roll out thin.
Cut into strips.
Drop into boiling broth and cook until done.
Dumplings may be cut into strips and placed on wax paper in plastic container.
Place in freezer and use as needed.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening (1/2 cup of which is butter).
Beat rest together and mix into flour/shortening.
Divide into 3 or 4 balls.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Lasts 3 weeks in fridge, months if frozen.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Bake until done.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Cool slightly.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup.
Pour cooled mixture over cheese; beat. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into an oiled fish mold and chill for several hours.
Yields 3 cup mold or 8 luncheon servings.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a 3 1/2 to 4-quart crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mash together.
Spread in a pie plate.
Circle edges with chopped nuts.
(I like almonds.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: lasagna spinach bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onions and celery in margarine. Add lasagna and meat; mix well.
Spread half the lasagna mixture in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Combine 1 cup bread crumbs and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle over lasagna mixture.
Place spinach over bread crumb layer, sprinkle it with Parmesan cheese. Spread remaining lasagna mixture over spinach.
Combine 1 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and margarine; toss.
Sprinkle over casserole and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves six to eight.

title: two-fish slaw
directions: Heat water (1 1/2 inches) to boiling in a 10-inch skillet or Dutch oven.
Add fish fillets and 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Reduce heat.
Simmer until fish flakes easily with fork, 8 to 10 minutes.
(Cooking time varies with thickness of fish.)
Remove fish, drain and flake.
Place fish, cabbage, celery and shrimp in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, 3 tablespoons lemon juice, salt and basil.
Pour on fish; mix and toss.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours.
Spoon slaw on salad greens.
Core tomatoes; insert a parsley sprig into each tomato.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Serves 6.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain, reserving grease for gravy.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir.
Set aside.
Add chili powder to hot grease and enough flour to absorb grease.
Add hot water, stirring to keep from lumping.
Add beef bouillon.
This will be a fairly thin gravy.
Add salt to taste.

title: layered shrimp salad
directions: In a large bowl, beat together cream cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and onion.
Spread mixture on serving platter.
Layer with desired amount of chili sauce; top with shrimp.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Scramble sausage until done; drain.
Beat eggs with milk and pepper.
Press rolls in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese.
Pour eggs on top.
Cook at 425° until set (15 minutes).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add baking powder, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg to flour. Combine ingredients except walnuts.
Add walnuts last.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Save broth from chicken.
Place both cans of soup and broth in saucepan.
Add butter and seasoning from dressing box.
Heat. Place dry dressing on top of chicken.
Pour soup mixture over dressing and let set.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jamaica cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; mix well.
Add all other ingredients except Cool Whip; stir well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip and finely chopped pecans.

title: salmon quiches
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300°.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: meat and rice(low-fat)
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground round or brown in microwave in colander.
Add to ground round in skillet the tomatoes and soup.
Bring to a boil and let simmer about 10 minutes.
Turn off heat; add Minute rice.
Cover and let stand about 10 minutes.

title: carnation pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie shell, until smooth. Place in unbaked shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°; continue baking for about 35 more minutes, or until custard is firm.
Delicious served plain or with whipped topping.

title: coleslaw
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, chop cabbage and spread out until about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Spread salt over the surface.
Do not stir for 1 hour.
Stir, then chop onion, pepper and celery.
Add to cabbage.
Boil together the sugar, vinegar and oil; pour over the cabbage mixture while boiling hot.
Do not stir until cold. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs and beat. Add zucchini, alternating the dry ingredients with the milk. Add nuts last.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove cake when toothpick test comes out slightly doughy.
This cake is excellent with cream cheese frosting.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, grated zucchini and oil.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake in greased cookie sheet at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: pickled herring
directions: Dress herring, removing head and tail.
Wash well.
Cut herring in 1-inch wide chunks and put in 1 gallon jar.
Make brine of 1 cup salt to 2 quarts water.
Pour over chunks and soak for 48 hours in the refrigerator.
Next wash the chunks with fresh water. Drain.

title: adventures(confection)
directions: Melt butter and sugar in a skillet (electric is best).
Add dates and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool mixture slightly; then add eggs, salt, vanilla and milk.
Cook 2 minutes. Cool.

title: trinity roast squirrel
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine lemon juice and cooking oil; rub into all parts of the squirrels.
Mix together the bread crumbs, milk, mushrooms, salt, pepper, onions, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco (if wanted).
Make a moist stuffing to fill the squirrels; skewer shut.
Brush with olive oil or bacon fat. Sprinkle paprika.
Arrange in a shallow baking pan; baste as necessary.
Cook for 90 minutes, until tender or well done.

title: down home limas
directions: In a large pot, add water, ham, beans, onion, celery and carrots.
Cook about 2 hours until beans are tender.
Reduce heat; add black pepper, salt and tomato sauce.
Stir and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: detrich sunshine corn sticks
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add 1/4 cornmeal; beat until smooth.
Combine vinegar and milk; stir 1/2 into cornmeal mix.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in rest of milk and vinegar.
Add rest of cornmeal and mix well.
Bake in oven at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn maquechou
directions: Put oil, corn, onions and peppers in large iron pot and brown until sticky on bottom of pot.
Add tomatoes, stirring and small amount of water to keep from sticking.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring often.

title: mary's salmon patties
directions: Separate salmon from juice.
Remove bones and black skin. Mash.
Place cracker between two paper towels to crumble.
Add egg to salmon and then cracker crumbs.
The salmon should be where you can easily pick up and make a pattie with your hands and it not fall apart.
Fry in small amount of oil over medium heat until brown on both sides.

title: *apple bread(grand champion demonstration)
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix in a small bowl the sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over melted butter.
Cut apples into thin slices and arrange on mixture in pan.
Add a few raisins.
Stir in a large bowl the dry yeast and warm water.
Add sugar, salt and 1 cup of flour.
Beat until batter sheets from spoon.
Add egg, softened butter and flour (1 1/4 cups) and beat until smooth.

title: chicken and ham casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Transfer to a greased 9 x 13 in. pan.
Top with chicken and ham.
Combine the soup, milk, colby cheese, and pepper; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix water and jello and let cool (until jello starts to thicken).
Add pineapple and pour on top and let set overnight. If using frozen strawberries, omit pineapple and add frozen strawberries to jello, using only one cup of water.

title: beau dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
This is better if made ahead of time to let flavor of dill come through.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil, then add 1 cup pecans.
Pour over cake while it is hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix thoroughly the cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Cover with ice.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Combine shortening, boiling water and milk.
Whip with a fork until creamy.
Add flour and salt.
Toss with fork until blended. Roll out dough.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: breaded mushrooms
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Dip mushrooms in mixture, then dip in Italian bread crumbs.
Do both twice.
Deep fry until brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together butter and hash browns well.
Add sour cream and soup and mix thoroughly.
Then add remaining ingredients.
When well mixed, place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Smooth out evenly. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Leftovers can be refrigerated and kept 3 to 4 days.

title: brown sugar rhubarb pie
directions: In bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and salt; stir in rhubarb. Let stand 15 minutes.
Combine egg yolks and lemon juice; stir into rhubarb mixture.
Turn into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking until knife inserted off-center comes out almost clean, about 20 minutes (cover edges with foil if necessary).

title: sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie shells 5 minutes; set aside.
