Mix sausage that has been fried and drained.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Divide in the 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: general custer's favorite fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice green tomatoes.
Dip in beaten egg and then in corn meal.
Fry in skillet until tender.
Serve topped with white gravy.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add Ro-Tel and cheese soup.
Mix well.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Crush chips in bowl; put meat mixture on top of chips and lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Mix up and enjoy!!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients and sift.
Add oil and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. At low speed add carrots, pineapple and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium heat. Add beef pieces and garlic and cook until beef is browned, stirring often. Mix soup, water and soy sauce and add to beef, heating to a boil, then reduce heat to low and add broccoli. Cover and simmer approximately 5 minutes or until broccoli is tender. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots for 20 minutes. Cream together 1 cup sugar, shortening and egg. Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and orange juice.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend well.
Drain apricots.
Stir apricots and nuts into batter.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan (8 x 4 x 3-inch) at 350° for 65 minutes.
Save extra orange juice cans to bake half full for parties.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat egg thoroughly with sugar, salt, syrup and melted oleo. Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix and beat well the sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.	Add cocoa and soda in water.
Alternating, beating after each, mix buttermilk and flour.
It is important to alternate these as you add to the flour mixture, ending with the one you start with.

title: homemade italian sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Mix again.
May be made into patties or stuffed in casings.
Freezes well.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown chops and set aside.
Slice potatoes and onion, alternate with layers in casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper; mix milk and soup.
Pour 1/2 mixture over potatoes and onions.
Lay chops on top.
Cover with remaining soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix the cornmeal with milk and let stand while you put the rest together and then add to the other ingredients.
In order to not have too much liquid, pick tomatoes from the can and let drain a little.
Put in a greased casserole and bake 1 hour at 325°. This may be made a day ahead or freeze.
Allow more time for baking then.
A good accompaniment to meat dishes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and shape into an oval loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Your favorite tomato sauce or brown gravy may be poured over the meat loaf during the last 15 minutes of cooking. Serves 12.

title: chicken sauté with curry and basil
directions: Chop the garlic.
Melt butter in a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and cook, turning once, until golden brown, about 4 minutes.
Add garlic and continue cooking for 30 seconds.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the cream, curry powder, and 2 tablespoons water.
Reduce heat to medium, cover, and simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 10 minutes.
Transfer chicken breasts to a serving plate and keep warm.
Whisk in remaining cream and bring to a simmer.
Shred basil leaves and add them to the pan.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over the chicken breasts laid on top of the rice and garnish with peanuts and raisins.
Serves 4.

title: tangy cucumbers
directions: In a bowl, combine vinegar, sugar, parsley and green onions. Stir well.
Cover marinade and refrigerate until cool.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until done.

title: macaroni salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except macaroni.
After getting mixture creamy, add macaroni.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze all lemons. Cut up 2 lemon peels. Put into a pot with 2 cups water. Bring to a boil. Add sugar. Let sugar dissolve. Strain into pitcher. Add 4 more cups of water. Stir. Let chill or over ice.

title: raspberry-cranberry gelatin mold
directions: Have one 12-cup mold or two (6-cup) molds ready.
Bring cranberry sauce and 1 1/2 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring often, until sauce melts completely.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until completely dissolved.
Stir in remaining 1 3/4 cups water.
Refrigerate until gelatin thickens to consistency of egg whites.
Stir in fruit cocktail and celery.
Ladle into mold(s).
Cover and refrigerate until set, at least 8 hours or up to 5 days.

title: chocolate pecan wafers
directions: Combine shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Add chocolate and blend. Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on well-greased baking sheet.
Let stand a few minutes, then flatten cookies by stamping with a glass bottom covered with a damp cloth.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix.

While cake is still hot, punch holes with ice pick or small dowel all over cake, going down to bottom of cake. Spread Eagle Brand and cream of coconut mixed together over top of cake and let run into holes.
Then spread drained pineapple over top of cake.
Let cool thoroughly.
(Put in icebox overnight if you like.)
Spread Cool Whip and coconut over cake.
Cut and serve. This cake can be frozen.
Serves 18 plus.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add to the first mixture and blend thoroughly again.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, powdered sugar, oleo, oil and eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, baking soda, cream of tartar and flour. Mix well.
Drop small balls onto greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruited macaroni salad dessert
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, salt, flour, eggs, and juices from oranges and pineapple.
Boil until thickened, custard consistency. Stir constantly.
Cook macaroni as directed and rinse thoroughly. Fold into custard mixture.
Chill until thick, about 4 hours or let stand overnight.
Mix in pineapple and cut oranges and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken breasts for about 30 minutes.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes, drain and put in single layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soups, mayonnaise and 3 tablespoons butter. Mix until creamy.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle grated cheese over soup mixture.
Roll Ritz crackers until fine, then mix in 1/4 pound melted butter until moistened.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Place bread in mixing bowl and cover with milk; set aside for bread to expand while chopping vegetables.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Form into balls.
Place in refrigerator to get firm, then roll balls in flour, in small amount of oil. Cover with water. Simmer with lid on until done, approximately 20 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: snails with tomato sauce(pomodori con lumache or chiocciola)
directions: If using fresh snails,
wash
under cold running water; rinse and soak for a few
minutes
and
rinse and drain.
(For canned, just rinse and drain.)
Heat
oil and garlic in medium skillet and fry the snails on
a
medium-low
heat for 10 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup white wine
and
cook
for
2 to 3 minutes. Add red pepper, salt,
tomatoes
and
parsley.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours on medium-low heat.
Serve
with
crusty Italian bread. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown hamburger, onions garlic, salt and pepper until hamburger is done and onions are transparent.
Add remaining ingredients except the tortillas and cheddar cheese.
In casserole dish,
place a small amount of sauce on bottom of dish. Begin layering with tortillas then the sauce ending with sauce on top. Sprinkle cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: mama's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.

title: potatoes croquettes
directions: Add seasoned salt to potatoes.
Divide into 4 portions.
Roll into shape of a ball.
Shake in bag with cornflakes.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tupperware pie crust
directions: Place flour, Crisco and salt in a Tupperware bowl.
Seal and shake real hard.
The consistency of this mixture should look like "meal".
Then add 6 tablespoons "cold" water.
Replace seal and again, shake real hard for a few minutes, until a ball of dough forms.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake(from progressive farmer magazine)
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line with wax paper.
Grease wax paper.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of prepared pan. Combine the cake mix and next 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix according to package directions.
Spoon batter over coconut and pecans.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Put pulp into mixing bowl.
Add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add sugar and beat. Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add oil, then fold in nuts.
Put into a greased pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Bake until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush the crackers; put 1/2 of crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Drizzle with 1/2 of the melted butter.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Add eggs, coffee, milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: hot pineapple side dish
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/4 cup juice.
Combine flour and sugar; add butter and 1 cup cheese and mix well.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crackers on top.
Drizzle with pineapple juice.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and top with remaining cheese.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: Add first 6 ingredients to chicken broth. Bring to a boil. Add egg noodles. Cook for 6 to 8 minutes. Add cream of chicken soup. Whisk until well blended. Add frozen vegetables and chicken. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until noodles and vegetables are tender. Makes 22 (1 cup) servings.

title: strawberries
directions: Combine milk with coconut, gelatin and nuts.
Form a rounded measuring teaspoonful of the mixture into a strawberry shape.
Dip top in green sugar and rest of "berry" in red sugar.
Repeat until all mixture is used.
Soak almonds in small amount water to which a few drops of green food color have been added.
Use these for "berry stems.
Store in cool, dry place, refrigerator or freezer. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen candies.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat well.
Add chocolate chips and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: golden baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place chicken in ungreased baking pan. Spread 1 teaspoon butter on each piece; sprinkle with onion, garlic salt and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased casserole for 25 minutes at 350°.
Feeds 3 to 4.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Let dough thaw.
Stretch into long loaf.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with garlic salt. Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp milano
directions: In large skillet, saute shrimp, vegetables and garlic in margarine.
Reduce heat to low and add cream, cheese and dill seed.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Add fettucini and toss lightly.

title: frosted salad
directions: Will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: easy crab vegetable soup
directions: Check crab meat for shells.
Combine all ingredients, except tomato soup.
Cook in crock-pot on high for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomato soup, then cook on low for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Peel and cube or slice potatoes.
Place into a 9-inch square pan.
Heat together the margarine, soup and sour cream.
Add cheese; heat until melted.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Top with 1/4 cup margarine and 2 cups corn flake crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sesame chicken with honey-mustard sauce
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix the flour and the sesame seed.
Add pepper to taste.
In medium sized bowl, stir the eggs and milk together. Add the chicken pieces to this mixture.
Heat the vegetable oil in an electric skillet at 350°, or use a large frying pan over medium heat on the stove.
While the oil is getting hot, begin rolling the chicken pieces in the flour mixture.
When coated well, gently add to the hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Serves 8 football fevered fools!

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in eggs until fluffy.
Blend in flour, oats, coconut and orange slices. Place in covered bowl or roll in wax paper and refrigerate.
Let set for several hours.
These will keep 2 or 3 weeks.

title: d.j.'s cornbread
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed on boxes, plus add 1/2 the melted butter and sugar to the mixture.
Pour remaining butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake in preheated 400° oven for 40 minutes or until cornbread is brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray a Bundt or tube pan.
Place nuts on bottom.
Cut biscuits in 1/4-inch pieces (1 biscuit in fourths).
Roll in cinnamon sugar mixture and put in pan.
Boil margarine and brown sugar on stove for 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.
Pull apart in pieces to serve.

title: nancy's beans
directions: Chop onion fine and saute in butter.
Cook beans.
Add onion to beans, cheese and undiluted mushroom soup.
Top with Ritz crackers that have been crushed in melted butter.
Bake at 350° until heated throughout.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Turn out on board and knead 5 to 6 minutes.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes on a floured surface.
Roll out and cut desired size with a pizza cutter.
Cook in salted water for 2 to 3 minutes or until done.
Can use any broth.

title: coconut pudding
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in small bowl.
Blend in 1/2 cup coconut milk and salt.
Heat remaining 1/2 cup coconut milk in medium saucepan.
Do not let it boil.
Add cornstarch mixture. Cook and stir until thickened.
Pour into 8-inch square dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add 3 cups flour (mixed with baking powder and salt) alternately with milk.
Add enough flour to make batter stiff enough to roll.
Roll on floured board.
Cut out and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: tuna dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese on top.
Bake a few minutes until cheese melts.

title: fluffy biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with wire whisk; mixture should resemble coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once.
Mix until dough follows fork around bowl.
Place dough on lightly floured surface.
Knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll or pat until 1-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in very hot oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 10 big biscuits.

title: quick and easy beans
directions: Combine all ingredients together and add seasoning to taste.

title: blue cheese broccoli
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add flour.
Stir in milk. Cook until thickened. Add cheeses. Cook broccoli. Drain and place in baking dish.
Pour the cheese sauce over.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles, about 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Combine meat and onion with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Wrap a slice of bacon around each chicken piece.
Place dried beef slices in bottom of square baking dish.
Place wrapped chicken pieces on top.
Mix soup and sour cream together and spread over pieces.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
May double recipe and bake in a larger dish.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Turn into a shallow, buttered casserole dish.
Combine cheese and chips; spread over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 375°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: turtle bars
directions: Heat sugar and Karo syrup to boiling.
Mix together cereal and peanut butter.
Pour sugar and syrup mixture over cereal mixture; stir together.
Press onto buttered cookie sheet or jelly roll pan with a high edge.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken into egg, then into bread crumbs to coat thoroughly.
In a large skillet, brown chicken on both sides in vegetable oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Pour 1 cup sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until cooked.

title: hamburger-cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and put in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dave's potatoes
directions: Rinse, peel and slice potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Drain. Layer potatoes, cheese mixture and 1 large can of French fried onions.
End with another layer of the same.
Bake 25 minutes. Brown top onions.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in small meat balls.
Salt and pepper to your taste. You can dice an onion, if you like.
Cook noodles.
Mix all together.
Heat at 350° in oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pixie pie
directions: Pat berries into batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: egg and ham casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix bread, ham and cheese in pan. Mix rest of ingredients except margarine.
Pour over ham mixture. Pour melted margarine over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bavarian dip
directions: Whip at high speed.
Chill before serving.

title: dorothy's dandy
directions: Mix together flour, softened butter and nuts.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: crumb cake
directions: Crumble sugar, butter and flour.
Set aside 1 cup for topping. Add cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, soda and salt to remaining mixture. Add milk and egg, then raisins, dates and nuts; mix well.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Pour in dough.
Add topping; crumble well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Cut each bread slice into 4 strips.
Using 2 forks, roll bread strips, coating all sides, then roll in coconut.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove at once from baking sheet.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add tomato soup, kidney beans, 2 soup cans water. Stir together.
Bring to a boil; lower heat.
Add chili powder.
Simmer 45 minutes to an hour.

title: shake and bake chicken(low calorie)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Bake at 350° on a broiler pan about 40 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: winter waldorf salad
directions: Mix ingredients. Chill. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate-filled cream puffs
directions: Heat water, 1/2 cup butter and 1/4 teaspoon salt to rolling boil in medium saucepan.
Add flour all at once; stir vigorously over low heat, about 1 minute, or until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until smooth and velvety.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients, fold into creamed mixture.
Spoon batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Mix nuts, brown sugar, cocoa and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on batter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool cake in pan 20 minutes before removing.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well. Combine cornbread mix, cottage cheese, butter, eggs and broccoli. Mix well.
Bake at 350° in well greased and floured 13 x 9-inch Pyrex
dish
for
about 40 minutes or until sides turn brown. Great with chili.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Add milk. Mix well.
Place on well floured board; roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in well-greased pan at 350° until brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and cook cake as directed on box.

title: herb-cooked halibut
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Take 4 pieces of 12 x 12-inch foil, spray with Pam.
Lay fish fillet on each.
Add 1 teaspoon olive oil on top of fish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken broth around the fish.
Divide mixture on top of each fillet and seal.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: seasoned flour for dredging
directions: Combine ingredients together.
If flour seasoning is used frequently for chicken, pork or lamb, it can be made in large quantities and kept on hand in a Ziploc bag.
The paprika gives a wonderful taste as well as making the pieces brown without frying them to death.

title: quick taco salad
directions: Step 1:
In a large skillet, brown ground chuck and onions. Drain.
Set aside.

title: hawaiian hamburger loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into a loaf. Bake 35 minutes, then place slices of pineapple on top. Bake 15 minutes longer or until done. When done, decorate with pineapple half slices and cherries.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Cube 2 slices bread; place on bottom of baking dish (oblong Pyrex dish).
Add chicken mixture.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over all.
Let stand 1 hour longer, better overnight.

title: candy cake roll
directions: Brush cookies with milk, then spread with whipped topping, using about 2 cups.
Refrigerate remaining whipped topping. Stack in groups of 4 or 5.

title: shake 'n' make ice cream
directions: Pour crushed ice into a large quart size self-sealing plastic bag. Sprinkle ice with salt and set aside.

title: swedish pepparkakor
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to the boiling point. When cool, add the remaining ingredients. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Chill and roll thin. Dough may be made the night before baking.
(Swedish cookie.)

title: cheesy bars
directions: Mix egg, cake mix and margarine until crumbly.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Beat 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over crumbs in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Microwave onions, celery and butter for 10 minutes.
Break up cornbread and toast in large bowl.
Add canned chicken broth and remaining ingredients in pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk or cream.
Mix flour, oatmeal, sugar, butter, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Pat 3/4 of this crumb mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan or 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes only.
On this sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped nutmeats.
Spread caramel mixture over this and smooth with a knife.
Sprinkle (don't pat) rest of crumb mixture and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cracker candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk, oleo and salt together for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and beat until thick enough to drop from a spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix well and chill.
Goes well with chicken and broccoli casserole.

title: 3 step cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients
and pour into a 6 ounce or 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Spread with cherry pie filling.

title: beef tips over rice
directions: Cut beef and onion into bite size pieces.
Place in 2 quart covered casserole dish.
Microwave until meat is no longer pink. Stir in soup and bouillon.
Heat until soup is smooth.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup oleo and eggs to potatoes.
Add salt, cinnamon and a little orange juice to make it moist.
Put in casserole dish.
Add pecans on top with rest of brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Cool potatoes. Add eggs, salt, flour and onion.
Mix and knead lightly until smooth. (Add more flour if dumplings fall apart.) Shape into long thick roll. Cut in small pieces.
Roll each piece into a dumpling. Cook in rapidly boiling salted water until they rise to the top. Simmer a few minutes longer until cooked through to center. Drain.
Pour browned butter with onions over them.

title: doughnut dessert
directions: Warm the doughnuts; put a scoop of ice cream in the center and add some chocolate syrup.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Drain juice from 1 jar of artichokes.
Use to saute onions and garlic.
Drain rest of artichokes and chop both jars.
Beat
eggs and add cracker crumbs, spices and Tabasco sauce.
Fold in onions, garlic,
cheese and chopped artichokes.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut into squares and serve warm.
Makes 40 to 50 squares.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Place in casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips, corn flakes or Ritz crackers.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: quick pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour fruit over butter and add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Can substitute apple juice for most of sugar.

title: melting moments
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Cream oleo and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Bake on ungreased pan at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar. Slowly stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Add pineapple chunks and mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Mix butter and cracker crumbs in small bowl.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
(This recipe is easily doubled or tripled for ordinary casserole.)

title: streusel topped sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sweet potatoes, syrup and peel until well blended.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon in medium bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: sticky buns
directions: Tear 1 loaf thawed bread into irregular pieces and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the mixture of brown sugar, pudding and cinnamon over the bread pieces.
Tear up the second loaf of bread and layer on top.
Cover with a wet towel and let rise about 4 hours or until raised.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Turn out immediately.
Nuts and raisins may be added with the brown sugar layer.

title: white frosting
directions: Put all together.
Beat at top speed for 15 minutes.

title: pasta with spinach
directions: Cook spinach in large frypan in 1/2 cup oil with 4 or 5 large cloves garlic.
Add red pepper seed, if desired, and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender; remove and set aside.
In same frypan, put in 1 cup oil, 4 or 5 cloves garlic, red pepper, capers, basil and parsley; simmer for about 5 minutes before adding tomatoes.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Pour over penne pasta which has been mixed with spinach and grated cheese.
Add some Italian black olives (if desired) before serving.

title: chicken volcano
directions: Rub
a small roasting chicken with a generous amount of margarine.	Season	it
liberally with salt and pepper.
Place the chicken
in
a
pouch
made
from	several thicknesses of heavy-duty	aluminum
foil.
Insert
a clean hot volcanic rock into the
cavity of the bird.
Make sure the rock is as hot as it can
be.
Crimp the edges of the foil shut.
Wrap the pouch in
20 thicknesses of newspaper for insulation.
Put the whole package in a heavy paper bag.	Leave for 3 hours and serve.

title: wine sauce
directions: In a skillet, melt butter.
Add flour and lightly brown until flour dissolves.
Add milk, salt, pepper and wine until sauce thickens to desired consistency.

title: strawberry pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Add Jell-O to water, dab of food coloring, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook slowly until thick and clear.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Prepare pie shells.
Cream cheese on bottom.
Fill with whole berries.
Pour over the berries the strawberry mixture.
Use whipped cream or Cool Whip on top.

title: zucchini provencale
directions: Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Pour off any excess oil. Add zucchini and cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes; season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings, 50 calories per serving.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Mix dry cake mix, butter, brown sugar and nuts with pastry blender or fork until crumbly.
Spread mixture in ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Mixture will soften and spread together while baking.
Remove from oven.
Stir with a fork until crumbly.
Mixture should crumble easily.
If crumbs are very moist, return to oven for 1 or 2 minutes.
Stir again.
Cool completely.
Crumble, if necessary, to break up any large pieces. Layer crumbs and then ice cream.
Repeat layers, ending with crumbs on top.
Store in freezer.
Serve cold.

title: chewy chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir cocoa and margarine until well blended.
Let dough stand 10 minutes.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until set (do not overbake).
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from baking sheets.

title: homemade christmas ornaments(not to be eaten)
directions: Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Poke with pin for hanging.
Let dry for 24
hours, then paint and decorate.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a wooden spoon, just until mixed. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Melt the margarine and garlic. Brush over tops while still warm.

title: banana fruit crush
directions: Combine sugar and water and bring to a boil until sugar dissolves.
Let cool slightly and stir in all other ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze.
Before serving, thaw slightly and then add ginger ale.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix tomato soup, salad oil, vinegar and sugar well.
Add vegetables.
Will keep well for 2 to 3 weeks, if chilled.

title: cheese roll-ups(makes 6 servings)
directions: Cook bacon and reserve.
Cut crusts from loaf and cut loaf into 6 horizontal slices.
Crumble bacon and combine with cheese, olives, Worcestershire sauce and 1/3 cup of the mushroom soup. Spread 3 tablespoons of the mixture on each slice of bread.
Roll up, jelly-roll fashion.
Place each roll-up on a paper plate. Cook one at a time on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until heated through.
Combine remaining mushroom soup and milk in a 2-cup glass measuring cup.
Cook on Bake for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes or until piping hot.
Serve mushroom sauce over roll-ups.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a greased 8-inch square baking pan.

title: quick spinach and sausage lasagna
directions: Prepare "Italian Sausage Sauce" for use in this recipe.
Mix first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Spread 2 cups of Sausage Sauce in bottom of 3-quart oblong casserole; cover with 1 layer of uncooked noodles.
Combine Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Spread noodles with half of Ricotta mixture and sprinkle with 1/3 of other cheeses.
Repeat layers; cover with remaining ingredients.
Cover dish with foil and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until hot and bubbly and noodles are cooked.

title: eastern north carolina barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Use to baste meat and to season chopped barbecue.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until fluffy; add sugar.
Beat until peaks (very slowly).
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Place on foil covered cookie sheet in spoonful drops.
Put in oven preheated to 350°, then turn off oven overnight.
Be sure to turn oven off when putting them in oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Add dry ingredients. Stir until moist.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes. Freezes well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, eggs, sugars and vanilla well. Add dry ingredients, chocolate bits and nuts. Drop by teaspoons and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grandma's "beef loaf"
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker crumbs, eggs, onion, pepper and salt together thoroughly. Dribble sauce on top of beef mixture in loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until juice runs clear.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Grind all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Buy a loaf of Pullman bread.
Trim crust off, cut slices into 3 parts.
Spread mixture on cubes of bread.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix in Worcestershire sauce to taste. Roll into balls.
Refrigerate until semi-hard.
Roll balls in bacon bits and place in mushroom caps.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cook in microwave until cheese is melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash to boil.
Put into 2-quart saucepan.
When soft, drain and mash.
Saute onions in margarine.
Now add squash, onions, margarine, soup and egg to corn bread crumbs; mix well. Season to taste.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: bible nut bread(nut bread ingredients are named in verses in the bible.)
directions: Put everything in bowl and mix together.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes and break into pieces in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and cheese.
Spread over potatoes; toss gently.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs over top.
Melt 1/2 cup oleo.
Pour over all.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease sides of 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Blend butter, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 cup flour.
Pat mixture gently into pan.
Bake dough for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Meanwhile, beat eggs lightly.
Mix granulated sugar and remaining 2 tablespoons flour, lemon juice and rind.
Mix together and stir to blend with eggs.
Remove pan from oven.
Pour mixture evenly over crust.
Return to oven and bake an additional 15 minutes until it appears firm.
Remove from oven and immediately run a knife around the edge to loosen.
Sprinkle powdered sugar through a sieve over the top while hot.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach
according
to
directions on package, but omit salt.
Drain
thoroughly, patting moisture out with paper towels. Add stuffing mix, onions, cheese, garlic salt, pepper and thyme. Toss
with	a
large fork until mixed.
Add melted butter and then
beaten eggs.	Blend.	Form into walnut-sized balls.
Bake on greased
cookie
sheet
at
350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: hot bologna
directions: Add vinegar, Tabasco sauce and red pepper.
Cover whole width of pan with peppers.
Boil this for 10 minutes.
Stir once or twice.
Let cool.

title: oatmeal coconut crisps
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla, then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in rolled oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cover peas with water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add the water, ham bone, onion and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and let simmer for 2 hours.
Remove bone and cut off meat. Return meat to soup; add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes.

title: one pot meal
directions: Dust ribs with flour; sprinkle with garlic salt.
Brown in heated butter in heavy skillet.
Layer potatoes in a lightly oiled 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, black pepper, onion and green pepper.
Pour milk over vegetables; cover with corn.
Top with browned ribs, covering vegetables in single layer.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover; bake 30 minutes or until ribs and potatoes are done.
Before serving, sprinkle with tomatoes and green onions.

title: bob's lemon pound cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box. Add pudding to mix. Bake as directed on box.

title: clear french dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered jar.

title: five minute hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish; top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Mix well.
Line 1 3/4-inch muffin tin with miniature paper liners.
Spoon 1 teaspoon graham cracker crumb mixture into each liner; gently press into bottom. Beat the cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well.
Spoon mixture into liners.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Place cherry preserves into a small saucepan. Heat just until preserves melt.
Spoon 1 teaspoon over each cheesecake and chill thoroughly.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Cook the sugar, flour, milk, margarine and lemon juice about 4 minutes in microwave.
Blend some of it with beaten egg yolks. Return complete mixture to microwave and cook to boiling temperature.
Cool and add sour cream.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine; will become firm. Roll into balls. Melt candy quick in microwave. Dip balls in chocolate and cool on wax paper. Makes 40 to 50 balls.

title: frank-vegetable medley
directions: Combine frankfurters with remaining ingredients in 2-quart casserole, breaking up frozen vegetables with fork.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour or until heated through.
Stir once or twice during baking time.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar which has been mixed with flour. Beat well.
Add butter and Karo.
Beat well and pour into unbaked pastry crust.
Pour pecans on top and bake in slow oven (350°) until middle is firm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cooks in a crock-pot!

title: butter cake
directions: Beat together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy. Beat 5 minutes on high.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold walnuts into batter.
Bake in layers or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: minestrone
directions: In a large pot, bring water and chicken broth to a boil.
Add turnips. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Add tomatoes and cabbage. Simmer 20 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix the mustard, onions, margarine and poppy seed. Spread on the bottom side of the rolls.
Put the ham and cheese slices in layers on bottom side of rolls.
Put top back on and then heat in oven at 350° until warm.

title: oriental hot dish
directions: Saute hamburger and onion.
Place hamburger in a casserole dish.
Rinse and drain frozen pea pods; layer over the hamburger. Mix the soup, milk and soy sauce; spread over the pea pods.
Top with the chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in microwave.
Add corn flakes and peanuts, folding in well.
Spoon onto waxed paper, shaping each one a little high in the center.
Let cool and lift off waxed paper.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in a crock-pot and cook for 4 hours. Delicious for big outside get togethers.

title: pennsylvania dutch bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Melt margarine, salt and sugar in 3 1/2 cups warm water.
Stir together.
Add eggs. Stir in yeast.
Stir in flour, making a stiff dough.
Let rise until double in bulk in large greased bowl.
After several hours, punch down and shape into rolls or bread.
Place in greased pans or Pyrex bowls (casserole).
Let rise until double.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
When baked, rub tops with butter or margarine.

title: knox blox
directions: In large bowl, combine Knox gelatine and the unflavored gelatin.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Pour into large shallow pan and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: alice's apple pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add egg and mix well. Spread apples in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and cover with first mixture.
Sprinkle with spices and 2 tablespoons additional sugar. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with water and bake in a 350° oven until apples are cooked and top is slightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Melt oleo in skillet; add browned beef, onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is sauteed.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, over low heat for about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: grandma gaul's fasnachts
directions: Mix ingredients in order and beat 10 minutes.
Let rise until double in size.
Roll out on floured surface and cut.
Let rise again.
Deep fry in oil.
Serve plain or covered with powdered sugar.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saut onions in butter. Add to shredded chicken with 1 can of chopped green chilies. Roll in flour tortillas.

title: stove top meat loaf
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.
Shape mixture into a loaf.
Spray skillet with Pam.
Place meat loaf in skillet and spread ketchup or barbecue sauce over the top and sides.
Put 2 tablespoons of water in skillet.
Cover and cook over a low flame until done.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: tiny cheesecake tarts
directions: Mix together.
Knead briefly.
Roll into balls; press into tart pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen for future use.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix together cream cheese, 1/2 cup margarine and flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 2 to 2 1/2-inch balls.
Press balls into mini-muffin tin pans to form little pie crusts.
Mix in another bowl the egg, brown sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Pour filling into mini-pans on crust.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Beat cocktail sauce into softened cream cheese.
Drain and rinse shrimp.
Fold into cheese mixture with wooden spoon.
Serve chilled on crackers.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Coat a large saucepan with vegetable oil.
Place over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, green onions and sherry.
Saute until tender and set aside.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan, add flour, stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Stir in mushroom mixture, chicken bouillon and pepper.
Cook.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.

title: fried cheese
directions: Cut cheese into 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Put in plastic bag and freeze 5 to 6 hours.
Dip cheese in beaten egg, then bread crumbs. Place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper and cover with Saran Wrap.
Put back into freezer for 4 hours.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: apricot date raisin bars
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, margarine, honey and coconut.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Cook apricots, dates, raisins and water in a small saucepan until the water is absorbed. Spread 1/2 of the oatmeal mixture in a 9 x 9 inch dish.
Spread fruit mixture on top of oatmeal mixture.
Next, combine the remaining oatmeal mixture with the sunflower seeds.
Sprinkle evenly over the fruit mixture and press lightly.

title: minted cauliflower
directions: In 8-inch skillet, heat oil.
Add cauliflower, mint, salt and pepper; saute until cauliflower is tender-crisp, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with lemon juice and saute for 2 minutes longer.
Serves 2.

title: salmon noodle loaf
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Add salmon, salt and sage.
Add noodles; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: In mixer bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add mayonnaise, vanilla and water.
Beat at medium speed about 1 minute or until well mixed and smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Mix with buttermilk very thin.
(If fixing garlic bread, add 1 tablespoon garlic and 1 small onion.)
Put 1 tablespoon of Crisco oil in an iron skillet, then sprinkle regular corn meal.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until satisfied with texture.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes; stir well for 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup; blend well.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add soda; stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Break into pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: church windows(candy)
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter together; cool.

title: jeweled cheese ball
directions: In 1 1/2-quart bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts. Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well blended. Shape mixture into 1 large ball.
Roll in nuts.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip fork into sweet milk and press down.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until lightly brown.

title: flank steak
directions: Stick steaks with a fork before marinating.
Marinate 24 hours.
Cook 8 minutes on each side on hot grill.
Slice thin strips and serve.

title: oven kalua pig
directions: Score pork on all sides by slashing diagonally 1/4-inch deep and 1-inch apart.
Rub meat with salt and liquid smoke.
Wrap pork in foil and seal tightly.
Place pork on rack in roasting pan. Roast in a 550° oven for 45 minutes, then at 400° for 3 hours. Meat will be falling apart tender and may be shredded to serve. Add your favorite barbecue sauce.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chow chow pickles
directions: Put all vegetables in pot with spices in cheesecloth.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are just tender, stirring constantly.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken.
Remove from broth to cool.
Debone.
Cut tortillas in strips and drop in boiling broth.
Cook until desired doneness.
Add chicken and serve.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake crust.
Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar and the eggs.
Stir in 2/3 cup pineapple juice.
Pour cream cheese mixture over hot crust.
Bake just until center is set, about 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix starch with enough cold water to make a smooth paste.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until glossy over a low flame.
Stir in dry soap flakes while still warm.
When cool, add glycerine.
Add paint.
Store in fridge.
Paint on wet paper.
Heavy glazed white shelf paper.

title: sandwich treats
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Cube cheese and melt in meat mixture.
Add spices.
Spread on party rye.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
These can be frozen individually.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
In a large mixing bowl, sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir until mixed (hand mix only).
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on rack for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: essie's pepper steak
directions: In a large skillet, place 2 tablespoons oil. Season strips of steak and cook in oil until browned.
Cover steak with bell peppers and onions.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring as needed. Add the tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Let mixture simmer for another 30 minutes.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk.
Mix all dry ingredients and pour marshmallows over all. Mix well.
Shape into loaf or pour into pans.

title: vegetable salad and marinade
directions: Salad:
Cut broccoli and cauliflower in bite size pieces. Slice carrots thin.
Combine all vegetables for the marinade.

title: candied apple muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper liners.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and sugar; set aside.
In medium bowl lightly beat eggs. Stir in applesauce and butter.
Stir into flour mixture only until dry ingredients are moist.
Add cinnamon candies quickly to keep color from spreading.
Spoon into muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Roll in a ball and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while cookies are still warm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: festive chicken spread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Add chicken, eggs, green onions and green peppers.
Stir well.
Line a 1-quart mixing bowl or mold with plastic wrap.
Spoon mixture into bowl.
Press firmly with back of spoon.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Invert bowl onto serving platter.
Remove bowl and peel off plastic wrap.
Garnish mound with toasted sesame seed, black olives and sweet red pepper. Serve with assorted crackers.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Heat oysters in
own
liquid,
drain.
Mix all ingredients, toss with fork.
Stuffing for 4 to 5 pound fowl.

title: best cake ever
directions: In saucepan, mix first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together the zucchini and onion.
Mix together Bisquick, Parmesan cheese, parsley, pepper and salt.
Beat and mix together the eggs, oil and Angostura Bitters in a small bowl.
(Bitters can be found in with soy sauces, Worcestershire, etc. or in the liquor department of any grocery store.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine everything except crusts.
Prepare pie crusts according to directions.
Spoon prepared mixture into pie crust.
Cover with top pie crust.
Cut slits in crust and brush with egg yolk, if desired.
Cover pie with aluminum foil; top with center cut out to prevent pie crust edges from burning.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 55 minutes until top is golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients into bowl; add milk, egg yolks, butter and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer or until firm.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets with vegetable brush and place in a large pot. Cover with water and bring to a boil. Boil until able to pierce with fork, then remove from pot. Take vinegar, sugar, 1 1/2 cups beet juice and pickling spices and mix together.
Place in pot and bring to a boil.
Peel beets, then slice or dice.
Place beets into clean and hot canning jars.
Pour hot juice mixture over the beets and seal jars.

title: pastitso(greek lasagne)
directions: Saute the hamburger along with the yellow onion in the oil. When the onion is clear, drain grease, then add the parsley, garlic, cinnamon, tomato sauce and white wine.
Let this cook together for 30 minutes.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Rub the fondue pot (earthenware) well with the garlic.
Pour the wine and 1/3 of the cheese into the pot and put on stove over medium heat.
Start stirring in a figure 8 motion and keep on stirring as you add the rest of the cheese.
Cook, stirring all the time, until it starts to boil.
Add cornstarch, mixed with Kirsch and bring once more to a boil.
Quickly season with pepper and a pinch of nutmeg.
Place on chafing dish burner.
Adjust flame so that the fondue will simmer throughout the meal.
When you dip your bread into the cheese, give the cheese mixture a good stir from the bottom.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Place sliced carrot pennies in saucepan with small amount of water (just to cover).
Let come to a boil, then boil for 10 minutes only.
Remove from stove and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight or longer.
Very good with beans and meat.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine in bowl the flour, egg yolks and milk.
Bring to boil the brown sugar, oleo and water.
Add mixture to bowl ingredients and boil 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool.
May top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: delicious steak and gravy in the crock-pot
directions: Melt the margarine in a skillet.
Flour the cube steaks and brown the outside of the steaks in the margarine.
Put the steaks in the crock-pot.
Then put the golden mushroom soup in a pot with one can of water measured in the soup can.
Warm slightly.
Pour the soup over the steaks in the crock-pot.
Cook on low six to eight hours.

title: mexican message
directions: Brown ground meat; drain grease.

Mix corn and soups together. At bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan, put the tortillas; on top, put the ground meat on top of that and pour the enchilada sauce, then put half of grated cheese and then the soup mixture.
Put the rest of grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Eat with chips like at Casa.

title: chorizo and eggs(my way)
directions: Brown chorizo in pan.
Scramble eggs.
Add salsa and chorizo. Spoon into tortillas.
Serve hot.

title: triscuit snacks
directions: Place Triscuits crackers on microwavable dish.
Slice cheese and place 1 pat of cheese on each Triscuits.
Slice pepperoni and place 1 slice on cheese and Triscuits.
Place in microwave and cook on High approximately 30 to 40 seconds.
(Note:
Cooking time may vary depending on your microwave.)

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Cool 5 minutes; then invert on plate.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with peaches.
Put butter in deep dish; melt in the oven.
Make batter out of rest of ingredients.
Pour over butter.
Don't stir.
Spoon on peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen lime mint salad
directions: Mix together crushed pineapple (undrained), marshmallows and dry lime Jell-O; refrigerate overnight.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Whip egg white and water together.
Mix in pecans.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together, pour over pecans and mix well.
Put on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes in 250° oven.
Stir.
Bake for another 30 minutes at 275°.
Let cool.

title: back to bed stew
directions: Spray a 5-quart Pyrex casserole with a nonstick cooking spray. Cut beef or venison into bite-size chunks and put in casserole. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Layer each of the following ingredients on top of meat:
carrots, onions, celery and potatoes. Drain and reserve juice from peas and beans.
Add the vegetables to stew.
Mix the reserved juices with the mushroom and tomato soups.
Pour over the top of the stew.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 5 hours.
About 2 hours from start time, mix stew.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat in well after each addition.
Stir in flour; spoon mixture into 10-inch tube pan.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: frosted holiday egg nog
directions: Beat eggs well with electric mixer.
Add sugar and salt and blend well.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Chill before serving unless the milk is very cold.
Just before serving, whip the cream and add vanilla.
Pour egg nog into chilled punch bowl and top with mounds of whipped cream.
Garnish punch bowl with a sprig of holly if desired.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: potato chip cookies(low sugar)
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar and vanilla.
Stir until fluffy. Add flour, potato chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart.
Flatten cookies by back of spoon.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan. Note:
When you substitute sugar for sweetener, cookies are softer.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Line bottom of an oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage over bread; add cheeses.
Combine both milks with eggs; stir in seasonings and pour over the sausage mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bring to almost room temperature and bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Mix cornmeal, onion, milk, corn and eggs together. Pour 1/2 mixture into skillet.
In remaining 1/2 mixture, add 1/3 cup jalapeno peppers, 1 cup hamburger meat and 1 cup grated cheese.
Pour over previous 1/2 mixture.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown beef slowly in skillet.
Add onions, cook 5 minutes. Put beef and onions in 8 quart kettle.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Bring to boil; cover, and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes, and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes longer. Cooks note:
This dish is great for dieters.
Best veggie soup I've ever found.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: An excellent side dish for ham, turkey or chicken.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Set ice cream out to thaw to room temperature. Crumble Oreos into bite size pieces. When ice cream has thawed, fold in Cool Whip and cookie crumbles.
Put in container with lid and put in freezer.
Let freeze for 3 to 4 hours.

title: date cake
directions: Put first 3 ingredients together and cool.
Cream egg, Crisco and sugar well.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add flour and dates alternately.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Add chocolate chips, sugar and nuts.
Put on top of batter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: black or dirty rice
directions: Boil beef liver and chicken gizzards until tender.
Grind and put back in the same water it was boiled in.
After all vegetables are cut up, add to ground beef liver and chicken gizzards.
Let this set until the rice is cooked.
After rice is cooked, drain water from ground ingredients and mix with rice.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix altogether and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sunday night fish
directions: Salt fish to taste.
Place in baking dish.
Combine soup, water, celery, onion and as much hot sauce as you like.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 300° just until fish is flaky.
Do not overcook. Serve over hot rice.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour over crackers. Mix well. Place in baking dish and put in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nanny girl's hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat! Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 9-inch cake pans which have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top, then sprinkle chopped pecans over.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in soup pot, cook over high heat until mixture boils.
Reduce heat to low and cook 30 minutes (or until potatoes are tender).
Stir in last 3 ingredients.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, start with stick of margarine, melted, and then follow in order.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and stir.
Place in a large cake pan.
Bake in a 250° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spray pan with Pam before baking.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Place potatoes in baking dish, then put the onion over potatoes; salt and pepper and make another layer of each if necessary.
Add margarine.
Combine mushroom soup and milk; pour over layers.
Bake for 1 hour in 450° oven.
Remove from oven.
Add cheese on top.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick butter; set aside.
Cream sugar and softened stick of butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour, buttermilk and soda.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Bake in greased, floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: grandma's molasses banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Beat in egg, molasses and banana.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: italian-style fish and vegetables
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Add onion mushrooms, basil and fennel seed.
Cook 4 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in frozen vegetables.
Place fish over vegetables.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Let stand about 3 minutes or until Parmesan cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: baptist pie
directions: Combine milk, lime juice and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts. Garnish with lime twists or more Cool Whip.

title: creamy fettuccine primavera
directions: Prepare fettuccine as directed on package, adding broccoli, carrots and red pepper during the last 5 minutes of cooking time; drain.
Stir milk, Neufchatel cheese, onions and seasonings in medium saucepan on low heat until smooth.
Stir in turkey and Parmesan cheese.
Toss pasta and vegetables with sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 3 minutes.
Set off heat to cool. Then add strawberries.
Pour into a baked pie shell and let chill good in refrigerator.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip topping.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a 3 quart flameproof casserole, saute sliced onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour to form a paste.
Pour in cognac, stir until smooth. Gradually stir in broth. Season with basil and simmer 30
to 40 minutes. Top soup with toasted slices of bread, sprinkle with cheese and broil until cheese is golden and bubbly. Serve immediately.
Serves 10 to 12. Soup may also be put in individual soup tureen and broiled separately for individual servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in butter.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Put in casserole dish or crock-pot and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or cook on low in crock-pot for several hours.

title: chunky hamburgers
directions: Cook potatoes and mash enough for 4 servings.
Form hamburger into 4 patties.
Brown.
Add tomatoes, 1 cup water, celery and green pepper.
Cook about 1/2 hour.
Make paste with flour and 1/4 cup water.
Remove patties and some of vegetables from tomato sauce.
Keep warm.
Add flour and water paste to sauce to thicken. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve patties with mashed potatoes and gravy.
Serves 4.

title: moon pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed, less 1/2 c. milk. Add cream cheese and beat well. Spread over cooled crust. Cover with cool whip. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: healthy pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in salted water (add few drops of oil). Drain pasta and put back into pot. Add chopped celery, tomato, onion, black olives, garlic and crab meat. Mix all together. Add a few drops of olive oil as needed. Chill and serve.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making 2 (8-inch) layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting and spread remainder between layers.
Combine reserved 1 cup sour cream mix with Cool Whip and frost cake. Seal in airtight container and refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: yogurt banana sips
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serves 2.

title: magetti-microwave
directions: Place browned meat in a casserole dish (large).
Place noodles over meat.
Mix soups, water, chili powder, garlic salt, bell pepper and minced onion; pour over beef and noodles.
Make sure noodles are covered with soup mixture.
Stir if necessary.
Cook 15 minutes on High, then 10 minutes on Medium.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: gourmet-basmati rice-risotto
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cheese in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring once after 1/2 hour.
Fluff rice lightly with fork and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven; finish baking for 1/2 hour.
Easy to make. Delicious.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Boil chopped broccoli; drain, then set aside.
In frying pan, melt butter, then crush Ritz crackers and saute.
In casserole dish, layer broccoli, then spread crackers over broccoli.
Place slices of cheese over crackers.
Repeat steps, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soft pretzel shapes
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Mix 1 teaspoon salt, sugar and flour into it and knead.
Give each child a ball of dough to roll and twist into any shape.
Lay on greased cookie sheets and brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot chili rice
directions: Cook rice.
Mix in chilies, sour cream and 3/4 of the cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Pat 1 tablespoon butter on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in uncovered dish.

title: "audrey's" hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a loaf pan and bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: raspberry fingers
directions: With pastry blender, cut butter into flour until mixture is like coarse meal.
Mix in sugar, ground almonds, egg yolk and almond extract.
Blend to a stiff paste, using hands if necessary. Press half of the mixture in a 9-inch square pan.
Spread with jam.
Roll out remaining dough (chill first if necessary) to a 9-inch square.
Arrange carefully and evenly over the jam. Sprinkle with chopped almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. While still warm and in pan, cut into fingers.
Makes 27.

title: lemon pie (custard)
directions: Add sugar to water and bring to a boil.
Add milk with beaten egg yolks and bring to a boil.
Add just enough water to cornstarch to mix and add slowly to mixture.
Turn heat down low and let bubble for 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and lemon extract.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: rolls
directions: Add together the first 3 ingredients.
Cream Crisco and add sugar.
Add egg, salt and water.
Add yeast mixture.
Add flour and put into greased bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Knead and put in refrigerator.
Let rise 2 to 2 1/2 hours before baking in a 350° oven.

title: chicken stuffing hot dish
directions: Cut up left over chicken or turkey.
Mix with dressing and pour gravy or soup over it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried peanut butter and nanner sandwich
directions: Mash banana with back of spoon.
Toast bread lightly.
Spread peanut butter on one side of bread, mashed banana on other side. Fry sandwich in melted butter until each side is golden brown.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, egg and 1 cup catsup.
Form into loaf in greased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Pour remaining catsup over loaf and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Combine soft margarine with eggs, sugar and flavoring in a large bowl.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add nuts, bananas and buttermilk.
Mix the flour mixture and margarine mixture together.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 400° for 1 hour and test with toothpick.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Flatten bread dough with rolling pin and lay on greased cookie sheet.
Make a paste of egg yolks, Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic powder, oregano, pepper and oil.
Spread on dough like butter.
Down the center of flattened dough, layer pepperoni, ham, salami and cheese.
Saute onion and green pepper. Place on top of cheese.
Overlap edges as much as possible.
Pinch edges.
Brush top with slightly beaten egg whites.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together; chill.
Great served with platter of fresh, sliced fruits.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix with 2 eggs and melted butter; pour into a 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Combine cream cheese, remaining 2 eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar, minus 2 tablespoons.
Mix well and spread in pan.

title: potato salad cauliflower style
directions: Steam cauliflower until tender, but not mushy.
Add eggs, onion, green pepper, radishes and peas.
Mix together the mayonnaise, vinegar, Equal and celery seed.
Pour this over the vegetables and mix.
This is a very low-fat salad!

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix yams, sugar, margarine, eggs and milk; put in casserole dish.

title: angel hair pasta with crabmeat sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add half and half.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in pimiento, salt, mustard, red pepper and crabmeat.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle with paprika.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Sprinkle more saltine crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until set.

title: velvet sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually and beat 20 minutes.
Add milk and beat.
Add dry ingredients, then vanilla. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Boil and debone 6 chicken breasts.
Layer along with rice and broccoli in a large Pyrex dish.
In saucepan, combine mushroom soup, chicken broth, Cheez Whiz, onion and butter.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes, stirring.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Do not stir!
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yellow cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs until crumbly.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour on top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan drops
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Stir.
Add sugar, salt and pecan halves.
Pick out each pecan with a fork and place on buttered baking sheet one inch apart.
Bake 1/2 hour at 275° or until thoroughly dry.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix 1 cup fruit juice and pudding; cook until thickens.
Let cool.
Add fruit.
Cool to room temperature and serve.

title: spaghetti puttanesca
directions: Put oil, garlic, anchovies and pepper to cook for a few minutes.
Add tomato sauce, capers, olives, oregano and parsley before adding spaghetti.

title: m&m party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in an airtight container until serving time.

title: e-z microwave peanut brittle
directions: Utensils: One 6 to 8 cup glass or microwavable container (mixture gets very hot), one wooden spoon and aluminum foil to pour mixture on.

title: crawfish boil
directions: In a very large pot, combine water, cayenne, onion, thyme, bay leaves, cloves, celery, crushed red pepper, lemon, garlic and salt.
Bring water to a boil; add crawfish and boil for about 6 minutes or until crawfish is deep red.
Remove from shell.
Serve with melted butter.
Serves about 8.
Great for a cookout, lawn party, etc.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: In large nonstick skillet, brown garlic, onion, parsley, salt and pepper. As it cooks, press the garlic against the pan with a fork to extract its juices. After 5 minutes add zucchini and tomatoes. Cook for an additional 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender. Turn mixture into a serving dish, sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice as usual and set aside.
Saute vegetables in margarine.
Add shrimp, crab meat and seasonings.
Mix soups well and add to vegetables and shrimp.
Place cooked rice in a large casserole dish.
Pour shrimp/vegetable mixture over the rice. Cover and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
This recipe makes 1 large casserole or 2 smaller ones.
One can be easily be frozen and used at a later time.
Just thaw and bake as usual.

title: ga peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove 1/2 cup flour and set aside to coat peaches and nuts.
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and oil; beat until smooth.
Add flour and beat well.
Coat nuts and peaches with reserved flour.
Fold into batter.

title: james baba ganouj (ga-noosh)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly oil baking sheet.
Slice eggplant in half lengthwise and place face down on baking sheet. Bake for 30 minutes or until very tender.
Cool until it is comfortable to handle.
Scoop out eggplant pulp and discard skin. Place pulp in a food processor or blender.
Add garlic, lemon juice, tahini, and salt.
Puree until smooth.
Transfer to an attractive dish, cover tightly and chill.
Drizzle the top with a little olive oil and sprinkle with minced parsley just before serving.
Serve with crackers or pita bread cut into wedges.

title: braised halibut
directions: In nonstick frying pan, heat oil.
Sprinkle halibut with salt, pepper and garlic powder, followed by rosemary and basil flakes. Arrange in frying pan and cover for 3 minutes.
Turn halibut and cover for another 3 to 5 minutes or until flesh is opaque and flaky when touched with a fork.
Garnish with minced ginger and finely sliced green onions and lemon slices.
Serve with rice pilaf.

title: quick rolls
directions: Fix lukewarm water; put 1 package of yeast in water.
Fix flour in bowl; put sugar and shortening in.
Then pour yeast; stir and mix.
Put in warm place and put plate over mixture.
When rolls rise, cut up and put in oven.
Cook at 400° and cook until brown.

title: tea biscuits with raisins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins and orange peel; mix lightly. Combine eggs and milk.
Add to flour mixture, stirring to blend. Fill greased 2 inch mini muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in batches as necessary.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: hawaiian kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat powdered sugar and margarine until blended.
Blend in vanilla and salt.
Reduce mixer speed, add flour and beat until blended.
Form into balls by using 1 slightly rounded teaspoonful per cookie.
Roll in nuts.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix the sugar, cream cheese and vanilla in a small bowl. Chill. Dip apple slices.

title: crescent cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until onion is transparent; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper.
Set aside.
Unroll 1 package of rolls and separate dough into triangles.

title: texas white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; set aside.
Beat eggs thoroughly. Add eggs to butter and sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, fruit, pecans, raisins and lemon extract.
Bake 3 hours at 275°.

title: pecan turtle cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, add brown sugar and butter.
Boil 1 minute.
Top dough mixture with chopped pecans.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Put chocolate chip pieces over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: fresh tomato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Set at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
Stir and refrigerate overnight.

title: spicy pea or bean dip
directions: Drain peas, saving liquid.
