Put peas, celery, onion, garlic and hot peppers through blender.
Empty into bowl and add mayonnaise.
Use dip for vegetable sticks and assorted crackers and chips.
(May add 1 cup sharp cheddar cheese, grated.)

title: rhubarb cake dessert
directions: Crumble together and press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, stir together the water, onion, celery and garlic.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Do not drain.
Stir in the undrained tomatoes, rice, sugar, chili powder, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until the rice is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Shred chicken meat.
Reserve broth.
In a skillet, heat oil.
Add shredded chicken, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and cumin.
Add broth as needed.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Adjust spices to taste.

title: corn cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients; add milk to make good consistency.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Grease pan.

title: fresh baked apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir in apples last.
Put in one unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine in a bowl; mix well.
Press over bottom of baking dish.
Combine confectioners sugar, eggs and softened butter in a mixing bowl.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Spread over cracker crumb layer.
Layer bananas, pineapple and whipped topping over confectioners sugar mixture. Garnish with pecans and cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Crumble sausage.
Add chopped onions and fry.
When cooked, stir in chopped potatoes and fry until done.
Scramble up eggs. Pour eggs on potatoes and fry.
Once they are done, stir in hash and fry all together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve.
Add picante sauce if wanted.

title: molded rice pudding
directions: Bring a saucepan of salted water to boil.
Add rice and cook 5 minutes; drain.
Return rice to saucepan, add milk and cook over low heat until all liquid is absorbed.
Beat the egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar until light.
Melt the chocolate and butter together in a heatproof bowl set over simmering water.
Beat the egg whites to stiff peaks, gradually adding 2 tablespoons sugar.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir by hand.
Pour into pie shell and bake until glossy and set (30 to 35 minutes).
Do not overbake.
Serve with whipped cream or sliced bananas.
Best served warm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour loaf pans. Sift dry ingredients in smaller bowl and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix, then add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Add optional ingredients, if desired.
Baking time varies depending on size of loaves. Check mini loaves after 30 minutes; large loaves after 45 minutes. Add baking time if needed.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Best when served hot.
Suitable for freezing.

title: grilled corn on the cob
directions: Remove and discard husks and silks from corn.
Brush corn with butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wrap each ear tightly in aluminum foil.
Grill, covered with lid, over medium coals 15 to 20 minutes, turning often.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute hamburger meat until well seared, not necessarily brown. Add chopped onion, pepper, green chilies and tomato soup; simmer slowly for about 30 minutes.
Line a baking dish on bottom and sides with corn tortillas.
Add a layer of meat sauce, then another layer of tortillas and meat sauce.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup and water; let stand a few minutes, if possible, then cover with cheese and bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: crunchy top potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cornflakes in a baking dish. Sprinkle cornflakes over potatoes. Bake one hour.

title: hermits
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Add fruits and nut meats; drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) about 12 minutes. Dates may be omitted and raisins increased to 2 cups.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: beef and corn cheese bake
directions: Brown beef and cook onion until tender; pour off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 35 minutes or until hot at 350°.

title: easy cheesy peas
directions: Stir soup in a small saucepan over medium heat until smooth; gradually add milk and 1/2 cup Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over drained peas.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over pea mixture; add crushed crackers over top of other ingredients.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of paprika over top.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 450° oven or until mixture is slightly bubbly.

title: crab meat dip and spread
directions: Soften cream cheese so that the first 6 ingredients can be mixed together with an electric mixer.
Add crab meat and stir to blend.
You can increase or decrease horseradish, catsup and onion to taste.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat after each.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in juice and flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes before turning out.

title: chocolate delight squares
directions: Cream shortening with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup white sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Add dry sifted ingredients; mix well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over batter, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and add remaining 1 cup brown sugar; beat until stiff.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: sharp cheese cookies
directions: Mix with hands, shape into balls.
Mash with fork.
Beat one egg white and brush on cookies.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and cooking oil until crumbly.
Add pecans. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumbs.

title: tiffany punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Add lemonade and as much water as it says on can.
Add pineapple juice.
Freeze in gallon plastic jugs.
Supposed to be slushy.
Allow 4 to 5 hours. Cut plastic jug in two to put into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Makes 36 servings.

title: pancakes
directions: Lightly beat egg substitute, milk and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend with wire whisk.
Bake on a preheated Teflon griddle.
Turn pancakes when top side is bubbly and a few bubbles have broken.
Can make blueberry pancakes.
When bubbles form, add berries, turn and brown on other side.

title: apple butter
directions: Be careful of your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When selected, give him your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle; others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This makes them sour, hard to get along with and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened kisses, wrapped in a mantle of love.
Keep warm with a steady fire of devotion.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years and years.

title: lumpia
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except lumpia wrappers and oil for cooking.
Take a tablespoon of mixture and roll in lumpia wrapper; fold ends well.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve with sweet sour sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients;
place in buttered 2 quart casserole. Top
with
cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Slice apples and place in a pie dish.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Mix together margarine, sugar and egg. Gradually add flour and mix.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix and place cheeses in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle jalapenos over the top and drizzle eggs over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When a knife comes out clean, it is done. Cut into squares.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: hot party cheese logs
directions: At room temperature, cream Philadelphia cream cheese, garlic powder and Lea & Perrins together.
Add grated cheese and pecans. Form into three logs, approximately 2-inches wide and 6-inches long.
Hold logs in palm of hand and sprinkle outside with cayenne pepper.
Roll each log in wax paper and refrigerate overnight. Slice and serve with Ritz crackers.
Great for wine cheese parties.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine with sugar, oats and chocolate chips.
Stir in. Shape into balls.
Roll into confectioners sugar.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: lemon supreme
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, then pour over warm cake 1 cup xxxxx sugar and juice of 1 lemon.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Place in greased casserole pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel and cut up peaches.
Place in oblong glass baking dish. Cut crust off of slices of white bread and cut bread into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Cover peaches with bread strips.

title: pizza peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds.
Cook peppers for 5 minutes in boiling, salted water to cover; drain peppers and set aside.

title: guess again carrots
directions: Pare, slice and boil carrots until tender.
Mash; add butter, cheese, salt, pepper and onion.
Place in buttered 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1 cup buttered Ritz crackers, crushed.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook egg, sugar, flour and pineapple juice until thick.
Cool and pour over remaining ingredients.

title: wonderful cheese ball
directions: Chill and roll in pecans.
This is a real favorite!

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix corn muffin mix, cottage cheese, eggs and
melted margarine.
Add chopped onion and broccoli; mix well. Pour into an 11 x 13 pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients until creamy.
Stir in soda and oatmeal, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Drop by large tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cookies should look very soft on top when baked.
Remove from oven and allow to stand on cookie sheet for a few minutes. Makes 150 to 175 cookies.

title: salmon fillets
directions: Put milk in a large reusable plastic bag with the salmon fillets. Let stand 12 to 15 minutes. Drain.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Blend butter and the 1/2 cup flour together in a bowl.
Bring cream to a boil in a small saucepan.
Blend in butter and flour mixture.
Remove from heat.
Add pepper, salt, bread crumbs and salmon.
Mix thoroughly and then spoon into a dish to cool. Meanwhile, heat a large heavy skillet over medium-high heat; add the 2 tablespoons butter and saut onion until transparent.
Add contents of frying pan to the cooled salmon mixture.
If the mixture appears too dry, add additional cream.
If it appears too soft, add additional bread crumbs.
Form into 6 to 8 patties; dust patties with the 3 tablespoons of flour.
Cook patties in hot vegetable oil over medium heat until cooked through and golden, approximately 10 minutes on each side.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.

title: spice tea
directions: Put sugar, cloves and 8 c. water in pan,

boil for 5 minutes then strain. Put 8 c. water and tea bags in another pan, steep for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags then pour into large pot add other pot w/sugar mixture, combine remaining ingredients. Store in refrigerate, heat a cup at a time or large quantities.

title: chocolate chip nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients; blend well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts. Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until light golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes; cut into bars.

title: vegetable fettuccine primavera
directions: Bring 8 cups of water to a full boil.
Add fettuccine and carrots.
Cook for 6 minutes; add broccoli and cook for 4 to 5 minutes until ingredients are tender.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter, stir in flour, salt and nutmeg; continue to cook until smooth and bubbly (approximately 1 minute).
Add milk, continue to cook over medium heat for 4 to 6 minutes, or until mixture boils. Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in vegetables and pasta, cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: crescent rolls(buttery-rich-golden)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm water. Blend well, add additional hot roll mix to make it a soft, but not too sticky, dough.
Knead about 5 minutes, until dough is smooth. Lightly butter bowl.
Put dough in bowl and let rise in a warm place until double in size, about 1 hour.
Generously grease baking sheet.
Punch dough down. Divide in half.
Let stand 10 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out each half to a 12-inch circle.
Brush each circle with 1 tablespoon softened butter or margarine.
Cut each circle into 16 pie shaped wedges. Roll up each wedge from the wide end.
Place pointed side down in a crescent shape on prepared baking sheets.
Cover and let rise again until doubled in bulk, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes about 32 rolls.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight. Mix before serving.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts, in large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until cake springs back.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.

title: frosty strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil the applesauce.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
Cool until almost jelled.
Add whipped topping; mix well.
Pour into pie crust; chill 2 hours or more before serving.

title: spicy nuts
directions: Mix all of the above and enjoy.

title: white cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening, salt and 1 cup milk in a large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add baking powder, egg whites, remaining 1/2 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into baking pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: english potato chips
directions: Make a double pan of foil on a cookie sheet.
Add salt and parsley to potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Almost seal the foil. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be cooked ahead of time and warmed up.
Freezes well.

title: quick baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions; drain.
In medium pan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; stir until melted.
Combine macaroni and cheese sauce; mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: six-can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except onion rings.
Place in casserole and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and top with onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° or until is set and firm.

title: ice cream oreo pie
directions: Crunch cookies up real fine. Combine together the ice cream and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze firmly in freezer.

title: corn salad
directions: In a large bowl combine vegetables.
Stir in dressing.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Good and keeps 2 or 3 days.

title: clams casino
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add crumbs and Tabasco and mix well.
Open clams and keep on half shell.
Top each with bread mixture.
Put bacon piece on top.
Bake at 450° until bacon browns.

title: dilly shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and rinse in cold water.
Chop finely.
Set aside.
Gradually blend milk and mayonnaise into cream cheese, then beat until smooth.
Add onion, Accent, salt, dill weed and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Stir in shrimp.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2 greased pans at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: corn-squash bake
directions: Cut up and cook unpeeled squash in small amount of salted water; boil until tender.
Drain and mash with fork.
Saute the onion in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Combine the squash, onion, corn, cheese, salt and beaten eggs.
Turn into a 1-quart greased casserole.
Combine and sprinkle on top the dry bread crumbs, grated Parmesan cheese and 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Bake for about 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Bring tomatoes, water, drippings, onion and salt to a boil. Add macaroni and cook for 15 minutes or until desired tenderness.

title: easy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Over low heat melt 1 cup chips with margarine.	Add flour and
milk,
eggs
and
vanilla.
Stir in nuts and remaining chips.
Bake
in
greased
13 x 9-inch pan. Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken slum gullion
directions: *Turkey can be substituted.

title: chili con carne
directions: Pick over beans.
Wash and drain.
Cover with water and soak for several hours.
Simmer beans for about 1 1/2 hours, until soft. In an 8 quart pot, put cooking oil and saute pepper, onion and hamburg.
Add puree and celery.
Spoon beans into pot, being careful not to spoon up any matter in bottom of pot.
Add salt, sugar, pepper, chili powder and garlic.
Add some bean water as needed, or add tap water to keep chili slightly fluid.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hors more.
Serves 10-12.

title: mama's apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Put in greased and floured pan.
(Double this recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: vegetable medley
directions: Slice fresh carrots; boil for approximately 7 minutes.
Add sugar, onion and chicken bouillon.
When carrots are tender but crisp, add fresh broccoli and mushrooms.
Let boil for another 5 minutes, then add cauliflower.
When all vegetables are tender, pour into a colander, draining all liquids from vegetables.

In the same pot that you cooked the vegetables, blend and heat the cream of mushroom soup and the can of chicken mushroom soup. Return the vegetables to the soup sauce and coat the vegetables. Add more chicken bouillon to your individual taste.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: banana bars
directions: Mix in order given.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Let corn bread cool, crumble up fine, add all diced vegetables, add bacon, sweet salad cubes and mix well. In large bowl add mayo, then add all dry ingredients and mix well again, you may need to add more mayo, but only enough to hold mixture together.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix and freeze.
Roll into balls and freeze again, then dip balls in crunched nuts.

title: garden casserole
directions: Place ingredients in layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Remove from oven; uncover and top with Cheddar cheese (I like the sharp). Continue baking, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: fruitcake-a-la marie
directions: Chop pineapple, cherries and nuts. Cream butter and sugar. Sift flour and add salt and baking powder to 3 cups of the flour. Separate eggs. Beat yolks and add lemon extract. Add alternately the yolks and flour mixture to the butter and sugar. Continue beating (beginning and ending with flour). Flour fruits and nuts with the remaining 1 cup flour. Add to the batter. Mix well. Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Pour batter into paper-lined tube pan. Let stand overnight.

title: apple crisp and o.j.
directions: Mound sliced apples in buttered pie pan.
Pour orange juice over.
Mix dry ingredients with butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mystery fudge cake
directions: Blend butter and egg yolks together well.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Sift baking powder and flour together.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla. Last fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: chop suey(my children's favorite meal)
directions: Cut beef or pork in cubes.
Saute.
Add celery, onion, soy sauce and 2 cups water.
Simmer; thicken with flour or cornstarch. Cook rice, 4 cups water and salt.
Bring to boil.
Turn on low. Serve.
Place rice on plate; add chop suey.

title: tomato-prosciutto pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease a large baking sheet.
Unroll pizza crust onto prepared baking sheet; gently press into 15 x 11-inch rectangle.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add cream and milk (more or less to fill freezer container).

title: gumbo
directions: Make roux in microwave:
Mix oil and flour and cook 2 minutes. Stir.
Continue cooking 2 minutes and stir until it is the color of a copper penny.
Do not burn.
In large aluminum Dutch oven or pot (not iron), saute onion, celery, peppers, garlic and okra in margarine.
Add roux, water, Ro-Tel and Worcestershire and season with salt and pepper.
Add sausage cut in 1-inch pieces.
Cook 1 hour.
Add shrimp, fish, oysters and chicken.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and arrange in greased 11 x 7-inch dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix 1st four ingredients and pat in bottom of buttered 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Pour mixed vegetables over top.
Mix 1 can celery soup and 1 can mushroom soup and pour over vegetables.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and bananas.
Mix flour with creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan 1 hour.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: In medium bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and heavy cream until smooth.
Slowly add powdered sugar, beating until smooth and creamy.
Reserve 3 cherries, chop remaining cherries.

title: mushrooms oriental
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook mushrooms in butter until almost tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce, brown sugar, mustard and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves, about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve as a topping for grilled steak or as a savory side dish.

title: coffee roast
directions: Make slits in roast about 2 inches apart.
Place 1 slice onion in first slit and slice of garlic in next slit.
Pour vinegar over roast, making sure it gets into slits.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, remove roast from vinegar and brown each side in hot skillet.
Place in Dutch oven or slow cooker.
Add coffee and additional water, if needed.
Cook on medium heat 4-6 hours or until meat falls apart.
Remaining juices make rich brown gravy to serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: ricotta cheese rounds
directions: Blend butter and Cheddar cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly.
Place by teaspoonfuls on a baking sheet and freeze.
When frozen, remove from baking sheet and place in plastic bag to store.

title: apricot cooler
directions: In a large pitcher combine white grape juice and apricot nectar.
Gradually pour in the carbonated beverage.
Stir gently. Serve over ice.
Makes 6 (6 ounce) servings.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine.
Pour into pie shell. Dot with butter.
Put lattice top on with strips of pastry.
Bake at 400°.

title: hearty beef barley soup
directions: Cut beef into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat oil in Dutch oven until hot.
Cook and stir beef in oil until beef is browned.
Add beef bones, beef broth, water, parsley, bay leaves, thyme, pepper and barley.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Add onions; cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add carrots and mushrooms; cover.
Simmer until beef and vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes longer.
Strip beef from bones and add to soup.
Discard beef bones and bay leaves.
Skim off any grease on surface.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: exquisite raisin pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, vinegar, nuts, coconut and raisins; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is light golden brown.

title: peanut cracker dippers
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate coating. Using half of the crackers, spread 1 teaspoon peanut butter on each; top with another cracker.
Using tongs or 2 forks, dip each cookie into chocolate.
Place on wire rack over waxed paper.
Cool completely.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and butter.
Pat in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat the 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Pour over crust and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat pumpkin, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, salt and cinnamon in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, stirring frequently, until thick, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in small dish.
Stir into pumpkin mixture; cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Gently fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour over baked crust.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares and garnish with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken, potatoes and onion slices in a long dish. Slice margarine over the top.
Mix mushroom and chicken soup with 1 cup water.
Pour over last.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 400° until potatoes are soft.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Melt oleo, add egg, sugar and milk; bring to boil.
Stir in nuts, coconut and graham crumbs.
Pour over crackers.
Top with layer of whole graham crackers.

title: shrimp or crab mold
directions: Simmer soup, onions and celery for 10 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin in water; add to soup and stir well.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Add 2 cans cooked shrimp.
Pour into mold pan; set in refrigerator until jelled.
Serve with crackers.
Food coloring can be added (red or green for Christmas decoration or another color for another occasion).

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into two balls and roll in paprika and parsley flakes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets. Press with fork. Bake at 350° for 7 or 8 minutes.

title: japanese-marinated chicken
directions: Note:
For stronger flavor, add 1 to 2 teaspoons ground ginger.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° or 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream in a 3-quart kettle.
Gradually add water with the desired color of food coloring you want.
Add oil and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Put on burner and stir as it heats until it forms a ball.
Knead a little.
Store in airtight containers.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Melt almond bark 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes on High, until smooth, in microwave.
Add peanut butter.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir. Cool 5 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Spread in pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook butter and onion until butter is melted.
Mix corns and beaten egg together; add to onion and butter.
Add sugar, pepper and rice; mix.
Bake at 350° until rice is tender.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Lay tortillas flat. Spread cream cheese evenly.
Layer the ham, cheese, cucumber, onion and tomato.
Roll up the tortillas. Cut into medium circles.
Continue until mixture is done.

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.
Slice and serve on lettuce.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix and spread in one 8 x 16-inch square pan or two 8-inch square pans. Score top lightly with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° for 1 hour or until brown. Remove and cut into squares.
Makes 60 to 75 cookies.

title: pesto
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor. Amounts may be altered according to tate (some pestos are very oily, for example). Keep in airtight container in refrigerator for up to 6 months.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: small tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon and vanilla.
Add eggs.
In each tart shell, place vanilla wafers and top with 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool, then top with cherry filling.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in 4 tablespoons of butter until soft.
Stir in 1 cup cream, 1 teaspoon salt and potatoes until thick.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In large bowl, combine beef, pork, egg, pepper and nutmeg; blend in potato mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls; chill.
Brown meatballs, a few at a time in remaining butter and oil for 15 minutes.
Remove meatballs from pan and place in serving dish; keep warm.

title: stuffed mushroom bread
directions: Cut bread with crisscross cuts.
This is just like scoring a ham.
Cut to the bottom, but not through.
Stuff with mushrooms and cheese.
Melt butter; add other
spices and pour over bread. Wrap in double thickness foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves well with steak or as an appetizer. This is also good with Cheddar cheese and ham chunks!

title: fudge candy
directions: In a saucepan, put milk, butter and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted, then add marshmallow cream and beat.
Pour in a greased pan until it cools.
Add nuts if you wish to and cut in pieces.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Add applesauce (fresh or canned). Add nutmeats.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Push batter up into corners of pan, leaving center slightly hollowed.
For well rounded loaf, allow bread to stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheesy stuffed burgers
directions: Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Cook onion in butter or margarine.
Combine onion with 1/4 cup of the mushrooms, bread cubes, the 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper with 3 tablespoons mushroom liquid or until moist.
Mix ground beef with 1/3 cup of the evaporated milk and remaining salt.

title: festive layered salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and cool. Wash and thoroughly drain lettuce; tear into bite size pieces. Arrange in an even layer in the bottom of a large dish.
Arrange carrots in an even layer over lettuce.
Add layer of macaroni, peas, onion and ham.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: taco salad
directions: In 2-quart glass salad bowl, layer hot chili, lettuce, olives and tomato.
Spoon guacamole over tomato; top with cheese and corn chips.
Serve immediately.

title: pistachio delight salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pudding mix, pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Stir until well mixed.
Refrigerate.
Use as a salad or light dessert.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix package and pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Blend together Ricotta cheese, vanilla, eggs and sugar.
Pour Ricotta mixture evenly over top of butter cake. Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Refrigerate.

title: play dough
directions: In a bowl, mix flour and cream of tartar.
Set aside.
In a large pan, heat water, salt, oil and food coloring to boiling. Mix with dry ingredients.
Knead well.
Store in an airtight container or Ziploc bag.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Soften and beat cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix pretzels and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13 pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip with cream cheese mixture and spread over pretzels.
Chill.
Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
Add frozen berries and allow jello to thicken. Pour over other mixture and allow to set.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Stir in water.
Measure flour and sift.
Blend dry ingredients.
Stir in.
Stir in pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill 1 hour.
